{"type":"message","id":"e0e8b856","parentId":"4e71333a","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:07:15.450Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yep, I recovered the Apollo state from `projects/apollo/`.\n\nAlso, on `MEMORY.md`: there is currently **no `MEMORY.md` file in the workspace root**, and I also don’t see `memory/2026-04-16.md` or `memory/2026-04-17.md`. So you’re not missing it, it just isn’t there right now.\n\nWhat I know about Project Apollo:\n\n- **Apollo is the main project we’re jointly developing**\n- It is meant to be a **local-first governing knowledge-and-operations system**\n- Core idea: **one governing assistant, not one monolith**\n- Short version of mission: **acquire knowledge, organize meaning, support action**\n\nCurrent state:\n- Project is in **Phase I Alpha**\n- Status is **in progress**\n- Focus is **building the minimum viable backbone first**\n- The stack is already running and includes:\n  - OpenClaw\n  - Ollama\n  - Open WebUI\n  - LightRAG\n  - Docling\n  - Browserless\n  - Crawl4AI\n  - n8n + Postgres\n\nRepo/workspace state:\n- The repo root is now the active OpenClaw workspace\n- The old nested workspace under `Intel/workspace/` was mostly archived to `legacy/Intel/workspace/`\n- Active runtime/config under `Intel/` was kept intact\n\nKnowledge/corpus state:\n- `Vault/raw/` has meaningful source material\n- `Vault/Clean/` already has useful preprocessed corpus assets\n- We decided to treat:\n  - `projects/apollo/` as the **canonical control layer**\n  - `Vault/Clean/` as the **supporting corpus/evidence layer**\n\nMain decisions already recorded:\n- Use the **existing docker stack**, don’t replace it\n- **Thin backbone first**, no heavy orchestration yet\n- Phase I is about:\n  - ingestion\n  - normalization\n  - retrieval\n  - grounded querying\n- Not in scope yet:\n  - multi-agent councils\n  - elaborate autonomy\n  - heavy UX polish\n  - advanced regimen/RV/media workflows\n\nImmediate objective:\n- Prove the **first real Apollo loop**:\n  1. use the Apollo/Aurelius clean corpus\n  2. make sure it’s retrieval-ready\n  3. verify source-grounded querying through the running system\n\nNext best steps on record:\n1. inspect `Vault/Clean` manifests/classification\n2. verify what LightRAG is actually indexing\n3. define the first retrieval surface\n4. test canonical grounded Apollo queries\n5. keep secrets/runtime debris out of retrieval\n\nHigh-value framing:\n- Apollo is both a **second brain** and an **operational assistant**\n- Aurelius is treated as the **first serious module living on top of Apollo**, not a separate unrelated system\n\nSo the good news is: we did not lose the project definition. The canonical Apollo docs are in place and pretty solid.\n\nIf you want, I can do one of these next:\n1. recreate a fresh `MEMORY.md` and session note from the Apollo docs\n2. inspect `Vault/Clean` and re-establish the exact next technical task\n3. turn the recovered Apollo state into a compact “where we left off” briefing","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b1e71c44819182e01184ff4205b4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":191,"output":690,"cacheRead":12416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13297,"cost":{"input":0.00047750000000000006,"output":0.01035,"cacheRead":0.003104,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0139315}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776398822278,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b1e69290819199405c269707e68e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"089f6946","parentId":"e0e8b856","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:12:06.421Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-04-17 04:12 UTC] right for some reason MEMORY.md has been deleted... we need to prevent this from happening in the future. insisde the workspace-apollo-legacy folder you can find an old copy of MEMORY.md which could give you some idea of what we've started. unfortunately its old by project progress standards but better than nothing"}],"timestamp":1776399126417}}
