r daily snapshots and ensuring automatic backup copies might help prevent data loss without needing manual intervention.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Improving backup strategy**\\n\\nI'm considering adding instructions in AGENTS to trigger automatic backups whenever MEMORY.md changes, since AGENTS are read each session. It may not be necessary to update TOOLS. I could create a one-time backup now and think about establishing a cron job or a git-based snapshot later. A straightforward approach might be to maintain a canonical file along with a mirrored backup at `memory/backups/MEMORY.latest.md`. It’s probably best to keep personal context in MEMORY confined to that folder.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_M7uZjOV3S9X46qqZ8HzRCqfm|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b3400ef08191bfe522c56e969e3f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find Vault/Clean -maxdepth 3 \\( -path 'Vault/Clean/projects/apollo*' -o -path 'Vault/Clean/projects/aurelius*' -o -path 'Vault/Clean/reports*' \\) | sort | sed -n '1,200p'","workdir":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"find Vault/Clean -maxdepth 3 \\\\( -path 'Vault/Clean/projects/apollo*' -o -path 'Vault/Clean/projects/aurelius*' -o -path 'Vault/Clean/reports*' \\\\) | sort | sed -n '1,200p'\",\"workdir\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_szRFZoq7qj02PTTJFDChPbHb|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b3400f008191b2a498fb2aed8151","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"projects/apollo/status.json"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"projects/apollo/status.json\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3590,"output":874,"cacheRead":17408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21872,"cost":{"input":0.008975,"output":0.01311,"cacheRead":0.004352,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.026437000000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776399151246,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b32f9c448191b56a762f975f21b5"}}
