{"type":"message","id":"47a73711","parentId":"f3950c7b","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:13:56.060Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3fCLqywFLQ5Dm0lKVyxXUJ33|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b37da9888191806548adf41fb851","name":"apply_patch","arguments":{"input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md\n@@\n 3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n+\n+If `MEMORY.md` is missing in a main session, restore it from `memory/backups/MEMORY.latest.md` if present. If no backup exists, reconstruct it from recent `memory/*.md` files and the relevant project control docs, then tell the user what happened.\n \n Don't ask permission. Just do it.\n@@\n ### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\n \n - **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n - **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n@@\n - Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\n - This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\n - Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\n+\n+### 💾 Memory Durability\n+\n+- After any meaningful update to `MEMORY.md`, also mirror it to `memory/backups/MEMORY.latest.md`\n+- Keep a dated snapshot too, for example `memory/backups/MEMORY-YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n+- Never delete `MEMORY.md` as part of cleanup, migration, or workspace reorganization\n+- If the workspace root changes, explicitly verify that `MEMORY.md` and `memory/backups/` both survived\n*** End Patch"},"partialJson":"{\"input\": \"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Update File: /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md\\n@@\\n 3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\\n 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\\n+\\n+If `MEMORY.md` is missing in a main session, restore it from `memory/backups/MEMORY.latest.md` if present. If no backup exists, reconstruct it from recent `memory/*.md` files and the relevant project control docs, then tell the user what happened.\\n \\n Don't ask permission. Just do it.\\n@@\\n ### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\\n \\n - **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\\n - **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\\n@@\\n - Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\\n - This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\\n - Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\\n+\\n+### 💾 Memory Durability\\n+\\n+- After any meaningful update to `MEMORY.md`, also mirror it to `memory/backups/MEMORY.latest.md`\\n+- Keep a dated snapshot too, for example `memory/backups/MEMORY-YYYY-MM-DD.md`\\n+- Never delete `MEMORY.md` as part of cleanup, migration, or workspace reorganization\\n+- If the workspace root changes, explicitly verify that `MEMORY.md` and `memory/backups/` both survived\\n*** End Patch\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":191,"output":371,"cacheRead":27264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27826,"cost":{"input":0.00047750000000000006,"output":0.0055650000000000005,"cacheRead":0.006816,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012858500000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776399227349,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b37bba8c819198c1472cdd21bc97"}}
