{"type":"message","id":"671ce10e","parentId":"60f4ada2","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:23:38.094Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ccYayi31aS9Nma7ETmek7Ebu|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b5c9b074819194f7083d857b1a37","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/README.md:51:#### Is \"npm\" an acronym for \"Node Package Manager\"?\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/README.md:53:Contrary to popular belief, **`npm`** **is not** in fact an acronym for \"Node Package Manager\"; It is a recursive bacronymic abbreviation for **\"npm is not an acronym\"** (if the project was named \"ninaa\", then it would be an acronym). The precursor to **`npm`** was actually a bash utility named **\"pm\"**, which was the shortform name of **\"pkgmakeinst\"** - a bash function that installed various things on various platforms. If **`npm`** were to ever have been considered an acronym, it would be as \"node pm\" or, potentially \"new pm\".\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/spdx-correct/index.js:40:// Common transpositions of license identifier acronyms"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":396,"aggregated":"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/README.md:51:#### Is \"npm\" an acronym for \"Node Package Manager\"?\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/README.md:53:Contrary to popular belief, **`npm`** **is not** in fact an acronym for \"Node Package Manager\"; It is a recursive bacronymic abbreviation for **\"npm is not an acronym\"** (if the project was named \"ninaa\", then it would be an acronym). The precursor to **`npm`** was actually a bash utility named **\"pm\"**, which was the shortform name of **\"pkgmakeinst\"** - a bash function that installed various things on various platforms. If **`npm`** were to ever have been considered an acronym, it would be as \"node pm\" or, potentially \"new pm\".\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/spdx-correct/index.js:40:// Common transpositions of license identifier acr