{"type":"message","id":"9bdf1227","parentId":"b6266ebc","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:23:48.357Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_yxgRbt5uU5fh4fLYn0Gn9auS|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b5d129a0819187b97dfa1345dba9","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Command still running (session lucky-claw, pid 903). Use process (list/poll/log/write/kill/clear/remove) for follow-up."}],"details":{"status":"running","sessionId":"lucky-claw","pid":903,"startedAt":1776399825339,"cwd":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace","tail":"ciding between heartbeat and cron for scheduled tasks\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:18:openclaw cron add \\\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:22:  --system-event \"Reminder: check the cron docs draft\" \\\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:27:openclaw cron list\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:30:openclaw cron runs --id <job-id>\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:33:## How cron works\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:36:- Jobs persist at `~/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json` so restarts do not lose schedules.\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:37:- All cron executions create [background task](/automation/tasks) records.\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:39:- Isolated cron runs best-effort close tracked browser tabs/processes for their `cron:<jobId>` session when the run completes, so detached browser automation does not leave orphaned processes behind.\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:40:- Isolated cron runs also guard against stale acknowledgement replies. If the\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:46:Task reconciliation for cron is runtime-owned: an active cron task stays live while the\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:47:cron runtime still tracks that job as running, even if an old child session row still exists.\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:57:| `cron`  | `--cron`  | 5-field or 6-field cron expression with optional `--tz` |\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:68:| Isolated        | `isolated`          | Dedicated `cron:<jobId>` | Reports, background chores      |\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:74:For isolated jobs, runtime teardown now includes best-effort browser cleanup for that cron session. Cleanup failures are ignored so the actual cron result still wins.\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:76:When isolated cron runs orchestrate subagents, delivery also prefers the final\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:88:is not allowed, cron logs a warning and falls back to the job's agent/default\n/app/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:97:3. Stored cron session model override\n/app/d"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776399828344}}
