{"type":"message","id":"ba2370fd","parentId":"7bf6e577","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:25:43.465Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Exploring scheduling options**\n\nIt looks like the cron directory might not be set up or could be disabled. I could check the state of the Intel symlink or look through gateway logs for cron API commands using grep. A simpler solution might be to use systemd for on-disk scheduling, but that might not be available. I could consider spawning a background shell using `watchdog`, ensuring it's detached from the session. This way, the process might persist even after a chat ends, though rebooting could be an issue. The user wants automation, so I need to think of ways to make this process more consistent.\n\n**Investigating OpenClaw options**\n\nI'm considering using OpenClaw's cron functionality if I can get the commands to work. It seems there might be an issue with commands waiting due to OpenClaw opening a TTY. Perhaps I could try the `--no-color` option. It's worth thinking that commands might be hanging because of gateway authentication or an interactive login requirement. I might need to use `openclaw cron add --json`. Maybe modifying a heartbeat mechanism could simplify things since heartbeats are already system events. I'll also check OpenClaw's config, especially regarding the gateway URL and authentication token requirements.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b63d93f08191a093d09e0f61949c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp4bZHFa8g5_sylEbf3xKkFSzqxFAwJytlWgp9fyRq5Ebw2rpyPtSz34-ab2exl5x5OCaMfIZRsc03dMoVKofrvhhVLrg7ynQvBbS59X3Ae8Pu588wDaG9MvJ95pLiT26W2nYtFCviE3OqZWD5FuUkRFufx4Cs1qiaFgJbLS9clEgNjJqSDd1aOcHQ8vUB8KQLYIw98nEjMPHRT0mRL7CgLBG1vscDsNXhBkeYpfD69NheBq8W4IzXOD2CcA6swui_7Wrc3I_uqHwjRJdnUwby9Y3f4cbrxr1D3DPGTiOrwEASGhtEnu4-_3CvaKR4uaxv13cLxNxtyidTtzUujwqEkDIyyNqlprCJWoHj4Ex6a60-vfHgYuA3atn9AScI4zcjmOVhLOpHtOBe9K-W6QBo6zeHyPJx6c2ryCE6BQzoIB2sbIz5aOq