{"type":"message","id":"9ec0b563","parentId":"c46ef490","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:27:42.383Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Patching memory scripts**\n\nI’m considering how to patch the script for memory backups. It seems like I can define a variable for the latest backup file and check if the memory file is missing. If it is, I’d restore from the latest backup and then create a new backup. That way, the script works whether it runs manually or via a daemon. I’m thinking about writing a daemon script, starting it, and verifying its status, maybe through logs. I'll work on these edits.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b6b161888191b2b6c8ea5c535b88\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp4ba6GzO98NUrrC5OAOHgzurFHp2SKUtooc61qiKlvbkaebCILVv_GHg_YV8a2seDM1YYhcCJzpfRq4ZlU4oRwUHa0IEZaOkiPgYKJAdJAtr15K0kd9ByDrUTdErozoFs_IJweL1YBAiZiYfKikzdb4Z9JDeTeew4jPOOtt-FZWb8QZNunbS46M_7iF5C-_Kv-SGVKdLWfUMSZk4rAnjfwAGIMEo1NlvrUoIPJu4AjxgG3ycVhuDEBHZB4qKC1o-QFb410oG13dZwXsg1qclRXcxcKE2qVQ76rZxYjfLR1M381-1nQn1igDctIQj3Sfmr_vQ4Kgp2JXvYk6jiSMGGtTh-ULhCReqn8kG5Y74LaUUrpznqkmUgBfO8jjXQhr0tw2dJQjWtC98mx4RiM4AhG7hKEf1HiAbji5FWfer3eeAIc5i7xzo6oucf0y191kkUgLRYwVTIgRLRBRYqwm_yb3C55OM4ZWzmC7po5WGExYmivMOER4yf9haVlRZQqd_6yowoiQEBvspoQj79-T73qKvJlFXzD9eK6i3wIsD1ca-76Z-cbSfGPJ9BI5w10eTk6z9_f7lqSn83MsYAj5NJWd_02ZNDyMrD-ESY1H1USOIManunIHsgOyoQ-Ftyx8zUdBKLg5CO6KVWsQERhugktyl2YH_1m5UbrD98-HOyi3SVdRhoVwTdzY4EvYYDURDJHOwHrae6rbo6H6rYtKTQuo5hu3mKe4nlcC5xEXOz_NomWlxtkRX1RLBCxnrUadEG67RCE1f8kAGpQapcoaZlGWL77paatdv6kNdzxa7KRynZIdV5punpYEmiO-2ueqBwGmfnUENyao1LoB_dBb8bItH_Ac2-2b7pNVh5nIXgi7bymLeWWa5X0sxR3JGSY2DGwlpug5etks8Bzaf87l5WL170DPM100UayBXqJjeKtRhg6kzrhyOGkgsFtOswOE5zdNICWGQIHLHrQ79dV6a2PLX075466Pivave_rTZ2OvTPgezhEXjA6logbEvX-HP3ZHEsHGHYT_JR-QM-KYSHEmGWcTvviDscKxgDk6RiZa5A5_hy8CR9vU15b83NNid3lPixwxXOL3uzyQV5G3xguKt9YeY9Tzq3E7O3Iu8mXT9rGF_vGD5lQDOs6d2WrK7PeC5fZroMSOs0WHriP7akQC4qlR3UmJ9wa33GZkZSkijjAjtTwiAL8oQppVR2FJf3OD57