QwsfwK4DnVmpi9bCSOb7URJPL7o9WUgTEoC0J4P096a87e1HdH8GPKoWcBs6hG9jq8rknQ9kuQdIjLviBQRDInVhbmaJ6U_79jNvrDyV3vgGiobG\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Patching memory scripts**\\n\\nI’m considering how to patch the script for memory backups. It seems like I can define a variable for the latest backup file and check if the memory file is missing. If it is, I’d restore from the latest backup and then create a new backup. That way, the script works whether it runs manually or via a daemon. I’m thinking about writing a daemon script, starting it, and verifying its status, maybe through logs. I'll work on these edits.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"I’m going with a lightweight local daemon for now. It’s a bit less elegant than OpenClaw cron, but it will actually run in this environment today, and I can make it self-heal if `MEMORY.md` disappears again.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b6baf5c08191adc602b09fde119b\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_paPqcWj4ZSRKx7Ly5S9EDKmB|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b6bb1c40819187bb5a6b6bcb47c1","name":"apply_patch","arguments":{"input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/backup_memory.sh\n@@\n ROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")/..\" && pwd)\"\n MEMORY_FILE=\"$ROOT/MEMORY.md\"\n BACKUP_DIR=\"$ROOT/memory/backups\"\n+LATEST_BACKUP=\"$BACKUP_DIR/MEMORY.latest.md\"\n STAMP=\"$(date -u +%F)\"\n \n if [[ ! -f \"$MEMORY_FILE\" ]]; then\n-  echo \"MEMORY.md not found at: $MEMORY_FILE\" >&2\n-  exit 1\n+  if [[ -f \"$LATEST_BACKUP\" ]]; then\n+    cp \"$LATEST_BACKUP\" \"$MEMORY_FILE\"\n+    echo \"Restored missing MEMORY.md from: $LATEST_BACKUP\"\n+  else\n+    echo \"MEMORY.md not found at: $MEMORY_FILE\" >&2\n+    exit 1\n+  fi\n fi\n*** End Patch"},"partialJson":"{\"input\":\"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Update File: /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/backup_memory.sh\\n@@\\n ROOT=\\\"$(cd \\\"$(dirname \\\"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\\\")/..\\\" && pwd)\\\"\\n MEMORY_FILE=\\\"$ROOT/MEMORY.md\\\"\\n BACKUP_DIR=\\\"$ROOT/memory/backups\\\"\\n+LATEST_BACKUP=\\\"$BACKUP_DIR/MEMORY.latest.md\\\"\\n STAMP=\\\"$(date -u +%F)\\\"\\n \\n if [[ ! -f \\\"$MEMORY_FILE\\\" ]]; then\\n-  echo \\\"MEMORY.md not found at: $MEMORY_FILE\\\" >&2\\n-  exit 1\\n+  if [[ -f \\\"$LATEST_BACKUP\\\" ]]; then\\n+    cp \\\"$LATEST_BACKUP\\\" \\\"$MEMORY_FILE\\\"\\n+    echo \\\"Restored missing MEMORY.md from: $LATEST_BACKUP\\\"\\n+  else\\n+    echo \\\"MEMORY.md not found at: $MEMORY_FILE\\\" >&2\\n+    exit 1\\n+  fi\\n fi\\n*** End Patch\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":128,"output":720,"cacheRead":52096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52944,"cost":{"input":0.00032,"output":0.0108,"cacheRead":0.013023999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.024144}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776400047796,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b6b0771881919f1359246a788eaf"}}
