st, then re-backs it up\n\nVerified:\n- daemon PID: `1090`\n- log file: `memory/backups/memory-backup-daemon.log`\n- latest backup: `memory/backups/MEMORY.latest.md`\n\nUseful commands:\n- check status:\n  - `./scripts/memory_backup_daemon.sh status`\n- restart:\n  - `./scripts/memory_backup_daemon.sh restart`\n- stop:\n  - `./scripts/memory_backup_daemon.sh stop`\n\nImportant note:\n- I tried to use OpenClaw’s built-in `cron`, which would be cleaner, but the cron CLI is hanging in this environment right now.\n- So I used a local watchdog daemon instead, which works today.\n- This should keep running while this OpenClaw environment stays up. If the container/service fully restarts, we may want to wire this into a more persistent startup path next.\n\nIf you want, I can do that next and make it restart automatically after service/container restarts too.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b6efe7508191a6c8fcda75b20c7d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":181,"output":369,"cacheRead":54784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55334,"cost":{"input":0.00045250000000000005,"output":0.005535,"cacheRead":0.013696,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0196835}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776400107333,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b6ebd61c8191873461caff0e3f97"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7aafec1b","parentId":"8db2412b","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:35:48.378Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-04-17 04:35 UTC] Alright.. perhaps we have been rushing into things a bit. One of the issues seems to be that the pc itself and/or this container will ocasionally restart, whether commanded or not.\nIn order to proceed with project Apollo we should probably have started with setting up the environment better. Please take a look at the workspace and project folder and tell me what you see. Then tell me what your understanding of the project is: in verbose terms: what do you think I want from the project end game"}],"timestamp":1776400548365}}
