{"type":"message","id":"02ee9188","parentId":"38c04069","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:36:05.617Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_WPda51g41nQjS4B6hUQSQcm0|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b8b56038819180b93920876d171e","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"47c08ec010a6ad182ca507bd242243a4503bd7c3f2a55878d3b2c6c2c472092a\",\n      \"path\": \"MEMORY.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 20,\n      \"endLine\": 41,\n      \"score\": 0.4354034036801238,\n      \"textScore\": 0.4354034036801238,\n      \"snippet\": \"## Canonical project continuity\\n- `projects/apollo/` is the canonical control surface for Apollo.\\n- `Vault/Clean/` is the curated corpus / evidence layer.\\n- `Vault/raw/` is the raw archive layer.\\n- Apollo continuity should not rely on chat history alone. The project control files must stay current.\\n\\n## Apollo, recovered project progress\\n- The running stack already includes OpenClaw, Ollama, Open WebUI, LightRAG, Docling, Browserless, Crawl4AI, and n8n + Postgres.\\n- The repo root is the active OpenClaw workspace root.\\n- The old nested workspace under `Intel/workspace/` was archived under `legacy/Intel/workspace/`, while active runtime/config under `Intel/` was preserved.\\n- The raw corpus was\\n\\nSource: MEMORY.md#L20-L41\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"MEMORY.md#L20-L41\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"33da1e1c89f1136e6065f242431acf0488a8528a5bb9dbaec466e4ef38536057\",\n      \"path\": \"memory.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 20,\n      \"endLine\": 41,\n      \"score\": 0.4354034036801238,\n      \"textScore\": 0.4354034036801238,\n      \"snippet\": \"## Canonical project continuity\\n- `projects/apollo/` is the canonical control surface for Apollo.\\n- `Vault/Clean/` is the curated corpus / evidence layer.\\n- `Vault/raw/` is the raw archive layer.\\n- Apollo continuity should not rely on chat history alone. The project control files must stay current.\\n\\n## Apollo, recovered project progress\\n- The running stack already includes OpenClaw, Ollama, Open WebUI, LightRAG, Docling, Browserless, Crawl4AI, and n8n + Postgres.\\n- The repo root is the active OpenClaw workspace root.\\n- The old nested workspace under `Intel/workspace/` was archived under `legacy/Intel/workspace/`, while active runtime/config under `Intel/` was preserved.\\n- The raw corpus was\\n\\nSource: memory.md#L20-L41\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory.md#L20-L41\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"720230c021a9b99ae353de3d3a43d7fb536c8eb7fa6b8695cfec973f0ca4c5df\",\n      \"path\": \"MEMORY.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 35,\n      \"endLine\": 44,\n      \"score\": 0.41666895900584766,\n      \"textScore\": 0.41666895900584766,\n      \"snippet\": \"- Prefer staged, practical progress over architecture sprawl.\\n- Reuse existing stack and cleaned corpus before building more automation.\\n- Do not ingest secrets or irrelevant runtime debris casually.\\n- Preserve explicit project boundaries: Apollo, Aurelius, Shared, Other.\\n\\n## Memory durability rule\\n- `MEMORY.md` matters and should not silently disappear.\\n- If `MEMORY.md` is ever missing in a main session, restore it from `memory/backups/MEMORY.latest.md` if available, otherwise reconstruct it from recent daily notes and canonical project files, then tell the user.\\n- After meaningful edits to `MEMORY.md`, keep a mirrored backup in `memory/backups/`.\\n\\nSource: MEMORY.md#L35-L44\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"MEMORY.md#L35-L44\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"3dee56a68b161b5d9874084bca3676b25109c3fb0fb783e321265cf6ba2aa309\",\n      \"path\": \"memory.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 35,\n      \"endLine\": 44,\n      \"score\": 0.41666895900584766,\n      \"textScore\": 0.41666895900584766,\n      \"snippet\": \"- Prefer staged, practical progress over architecture sprawl.\\n- Reuse existing stack and cleaned corpus before building mor