{"type":"message","id":"014462dd","parentId":"a0baa1bf","timestamp":"2026-04-17T04:41:23.603Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Inspecting service health**\n\nI need to do a deeper inspection, possibly checking compose restart policies and the health of services, as well as the existence of the `.env` file and its contents. I could use `grep -n 'restart:' docker-compose.yaml`, but maybe that’s not necessary. Also, I should check if the services are running and look into permissions related to a safe directory. Running commands like `docker ps` will help me list running containers. Additionally, I might want to verify the existence of `.git` and use `git status --short` to note anything relevant. Let's see what I can find!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1b9eac390819182755b95e1b6cfc2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp4bnwux-BnnBMKXruabuANWcWjnTeOUbrq8pEUnoXjI4ViMVzNl7KtAkA04MM0-0wGVXItnRb516eQmPLe4iTA-ECh9rMNfBkF9k9WQUKAcY1M7kVnIXfla76V3DAiMevwktIv0niodJyoXpLAmA23tLBYSV_DwZLoE9gLIbP-XJBP6lVNqNBcqyoG0afVKyQUdC4_YBhFQRJlUXHB3q8m1ppHgorpRdNkQuWMCxWE7iCfdTaAOJ4frNWQPUCcigsLVfWONmOtTc2uzZI72xPgbTh3ASHtX4yqQ7cPc53XEFxBTNqsPaUNOJLJjbPCf6DYJTsVZqaAlLYpr26e73l6IHLkOWh1RjIbFsc555KHcPwOs4rv0RVngqn39Po_o43og6qZ01kgGX3CzKX5M5_fqW6WCR9AYIf7z-g6X9aGEmxZjNGhCxZU13EAJ532A8v8XGXVe_GEO0HVgKOwFyyiGSEftHgb3kRgQPX_zY_37iTOqHbI04KWTFMs6sDFUuf2C60BacK9CYp3Kc9UUAkBG610Udac69XySLKWszaaQyYEB-SPGl5p87SwFlkvI6CeehZ4ge_CqjzJmsd_jT4L6LCN9lJawW32n1ubv8ILsfewgVzo9RKAXYGyelRnTdpV0JYotOwfFji3wO57QrekrktA5wzw21LUmy__QdSS-5oDUCDkWz6dPt-y9dz2vMzzZRfz-sPflA6iu1-3x8KWtMOd5TmPP4ID26CdpDl_KTqDN_Q_2bM8h3mXfwtljFv93xaSP3xKoZNTOcYjcKHVx971z8qYLYtzL6nUIxjy05A8sU1auLFMXvzw_V31UpeB15mdhl_TnrS9L-LtUe4rzf73uVk983PjBq9UjM5y-hzrpRS5KRnchGnVoa-U657fGTkvUOzesDpoD5XHZ8g4n6Oxjo23F8tGPMAbWic_TF9hmMblThk3YHUQ6jDwXan_7MPpoOAoFQNirdZMvktqRNDRcrDCXNKBE_irYnPMEZrHnjJTPzrnAytIFKWtn8sKJLPOCE9GkoAyTwq2uJXNstTQog3JjV6aRa6iGYiLNGXgHrNE8H0T53oxVPf