 answer should include exact changes, sample patch snippets, and maybe a bullet list with a YAML skeleton, while ensuring I don’t actually edit anything without permission. I wonder if I should also address any external remote access concerns.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Outlining Patch Plan for Docker Compose**\\n\\nI’m focusing on proposing a patch plan for standby and restarts. It's important to note that on Windows, I might suggest using local bind to 127.0.0.1 for local-only scenarios. If remote access is required, I’ll keep 0.0.0.0. For ensuring survival through restarts, I should suggest changes like restart policies, stop_grace_period, health checks, and version pinning.\\n\\nI'll also clarify that the `deploy` section is generally ignored outside of swarm mode. If using NVIDIA on Windows, I may need to mention device requests too. I plan to provide a patched YAML excerpt as an example, reminding the user that health checks require the necessary tools inside images or an alternative solution if they aren't available.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Suggesting Healthcheck Options**\\n\\nI can propose using tools like wget, curl, or bash for health checks. If bash is available, I might suggest using CMD-SHELL with a command like `bash -lc 'printf \\\"\\\" >/dev/tcp/127.0.0.1/port'`. However, not all images will have bash, and `curl` might not be installed either. I could mention that my health check method might need to adjust based on the available tools inside each image. Since the user asked for a patch, I should ideally show a general pattern for implementation.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Docker commands**\\n\\nI should think about mentioning the difference between the older `docker-compose` command and the newer `docker compose` command that uses plugins. However, that might not be central to my point. There's also the concept of `stop_signal`, but I'm not sure if that's necessary to include. I want to keep it clear and focused, so I’ll weigh the importance of each element before finalizing my response.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Structuring configuration**\\n\\nI need to remind myself not to set all ports to 127.0.0.1 when using a remote phone. That seems conditional. Maybe I should structure things more clearly, with a core patch set and an example compose diff. Since the user mentioned getting lost, I could keep it compact and include only the changed sections.\\n\\nOh, and I should highlight that n8n isn't configured for Postgres right now. It might be useful to add a top-level `x-service-defaults` anchor to reduce repetition. Then I can apply those defaults to all long-lived services and add health checks individually. I'll need to pay attention to YAML anchor placement too!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Short version: I’d patch it in 5 ways.\n\n## 1. Make every long-lived service restart automatically\nAdd to **all** core services:\n\n```yaml\nrestart: unless-stopped\ninit: true\n```\n\nRight now you’re missing restart policy on:\n- `docling`\n- `lightrag`\n- `n8n`\n- `n8n_db`\n- `open-webui`\n\nI’d also add:\n\n```yaml\nstop_grace_period: 30s\n```\n\nAnd for Postgres maybe:\n\n```yaml\nstop_grace_period: 60s\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Add healthchecks and gate dependencies on health\nNot just start order, actual readiness.\n\nExample first-pass pattern:\n\n```yaml\nollama:\n  restart: unless-stopped\n  init: true\n  stop_grace_period: 60s\n  healthcheck:\n    test: [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags >/dev/null || exit 1\"]\n    interval: 30s\n    timeout: 10s\n    retries: 10\n    start_period: 60s\n```\n\n```yaml\napollo-agent:\n  restart: unless-stopped\n  init: true\n  stop_grace_period: 45s\n  depends_on:\n    ollama:\n      condition: service_healthy\n```\n\n```yaml\nn8n_db:\n  restart: unless-stopped\n  init: true\n  stop_grace_period: 60s\n  healthcheck:\n    test: [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"pg_isready -U $$POSTGRES_USER -d $$POSTGRES_DB\"]\n    interval: 20s\n    timeout: 5s\n    retries: 10\n    start_period: 20s\n```\n\n```yaml\nn8n:\n  restart: unless-stopped\n  init: true\n  stop_grace_period: 45s\n  depends_on:\n    n8n_db:\n      condition: service_healthy\n```\n\nSame idea for:\n- `lightrag`\n- `open-webui`\n- `docling`\n\nImportant nuance: healthchecks help detect bad state and improve startup order, but Docker Compose does **not** automatically restart a container just because it turns unhealthy. So this hardens reboot/startup, but not every hang-after-standby case by itself.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Move secrets out of compose\nI would remove inline secrets from `docker-compose.yaml`:\n\nCurrent problems:\n- `POSTGRES_PASSWORD: \"secure_password_2026\"`\n- `WEBUI_SECRET_KEY: \"apollo_v2_secret\"`\n\nUse `.env` instead:\n\n```env\nAPOLLO_TOKEN=...\nPOSTGRES_PASSWORD=...\nWEBUI_SECRET_KEY=...\n```\n\nAnd compose:\n\n```yaml\nGATEWAY_TOKEN: \"${APOLLO_TOKEN}\"\nPOSTGRES_PASSWORD: \"${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}\"\nWEBUI_SECRET_KEY: \"${WEBUI_SECRET_KEY}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Fix the `n8n` / Postgres setup\nRight now, `n8n` depends on `n8n_db`, but I do **not** see `n8n` configured to actually use Postgres.\n\nSo `n8n_db` may be effectively unused.\n\nI’d patch `n8n` like this:\n\n```yaml\nn8n:\n  environment:\n    N8N_HOST: \"0.0.0.0\"\n    N8N_PORT: \"5678\"\n    N8N_RUNNERS_ENABLED: \"true\"\n    DB_TYPE: \"postgresdb\"\n    DB_POSTGRESDB_HOST: \"n8n_db\"\n    DB_POSTGRESDB_PORT: \"5432\"\n    DB_POSTGRESDB_DATABASE: \"apollo_state\"\n    DB_POSTGRESDB_USER: \"apollo_admin\"\n    DB_POSTGRESDB_PASSWORD: \"${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}\"\n```\n\nThat one matters a lot.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Restrict port exposure if this is local-first\nIf you do **not** need LAN access, I’d change:\n\n```yaml\n- \"11434:11434\"\n```\n\nto:\n\n```yaml\n- \"127.0.0.1:11434:11434\"\n```\n\nSame for:\n- 18789\n- 3000\n- 9621\n- 5001\n- 5678\n- 11235\n- 3003\n\nIf you do need phone/LAN/remote access, keep broader binds where needed.\n\n---\n\n# What I would actually patch, concretely\n\nIf I were doing a first hardening pass, I would:\n\n1. add `restart`, `init`, and `stop_grace_period` to every service\n2. add healthchecks to `ollama`, `n8n_db`, `n8n`, `open-webui`, `lightrag`, `apollo-agent`\n3. convert `depends_on` to health-gated dependencies\n4. move secrets into `.env`\n5. configure `n8n` to really use Postgres\n6. optionally bind ports to `127.0.0.1`\n7. later, pin image versions after the hardened stack is tested\n\n---\n\n## Minimal example shape\n\nSomething like:\n\n```yaml\nservices:\n  ollama:\n    image: ollama/ollama:latest\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 60s\n    healthcheck:\n      test: [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags >/dev/null || exit 1\"]\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 60s\n\n  apollo-agent:\n    image: ghcr.io/openclaw/openclaw:latest\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 45s\n    environment:\n      GATEWAY_TOKEN: \"${APOLLO_TOKEN}\"\n    depends_on:\n      ollama:\n        condition: service_healthy\n\n  n8n_db:\n    image: postgres:16\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 60s\n    environment:\n      POSTGRES_USER: \"apollo_admin\"\n      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: \"${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}\"\n      POSTGRES_DB: \"apollo_state\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test: [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"pg_isready -U $$POSTGRES_USER -d $$POSTGRES_DB\"]\n      interval: 20s\n      timeout: 5s\n      retries: 10\n```\n\n---\n\n## One blunt caveat\nIf your main concern is **resume from standby**, compose hardening helps, but it may not be enough on its own.\n\nWhy:\n- reboot/restart resilience, yes\n- service ordering/readiness, yes\n- hung-but-still-running containers after standby, **not always**\n\nFor that, the batch scripts should probably become:\n- startup validator\n- shutdown validator\n- maybe a health-based recovery routine\n\nSo my recommendation is:\n\n1. patch compose first\n2. then rewrite `apollo_up.bat` / `apollo_down.bat` around health checks\n\nIf you want, I can draft the **exact patched `docker-compose.yaml`** next.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1ca7c6a448191acaa0ba9377ecf96\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":79583,"output":3587,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83170,"cost":{"input":0.1989575,"output":0.053805,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.2527625}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776405076385,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1ca55411081918d6110858b38cc62"}}
