\n\\nAlso created project buckets:\\n- `vault/Clean/projects/apollo/sources/`\\n- `vault/Clean/projects/aurelius/sources/`\\n- `vault/Clean/projects/other/sources/`\\n\\nCurrent first-pass classification:\\n- **Apollo:** 5 files\\n- **Aurelius:** 40 files\\n- **Other:** 24 files\\n\\nImportant finding:\\n- there are **19 exact duplicate groups**\\n- and **9 probable duplicate groups**\\n- so I’m glad we didn’t jump straight into ingestion\\n\\nOne useful catch:\\n- some likely Apollo and Aurelius files landed in `other` because the current bucketing is intentionally conservative\\n- for example:\\n  - `6 Prior Art Analysis Project Apol-...txt`\\n  - `7 Technical Analysis of the Janua-...txt`\\n  - `AURELIUS_CXO_v1.30...`\\n  - `MyActivity.html`\\n\\nSo the next step should be a **refinement pass**, not ingestion yet.\\n\\nMy recommendation for what I do next:\\n1. **refine classification**\\n   - re-bucket obvious Apollo/Aurelius files from `other`\\n   - treat `MyActivity.html` and `gemini_conversations_clean.md` as shared conversation sources to be project-sliced\\n\\n2. **canonicalize duplicates**\\n   - pick one preferred copy per duplicate set\\n   - mark the others as aliases/suppressed\\n\\n3. **generate project timelines**\\n   - Apollo timeline\\n   - Aurelius timeline\\n\\nThat will give us the clean base for LightRAG ingestion.\\n\\nOne small blocker:\\n- I tried to commit the changes, but git refused because the repo is marked as a dubious ownership directory.\\n- The exact fix would be:\\n  - `git config --global --add safe.directory /home/node/.openclaw/workspace`\\n\\nI have **not** run that because it changes git config.\\n\\nIf you want, I can proceed now with:\\n1. **classification refinement + duplicate canonicalization**\\n2. **project timeline generation**\\n3. **both**\\n\\nI recommend **3**.\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0beebb82725bec5a0169e09739abc8819192cbea87d88f02b4\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"usage\":{\"input\":195,\"output\":496,\"cacheRead\":45824,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":46515,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.00048750000000000003,\"output\":0.00744,\"cacheRead\":0.011456,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.019383499999999998}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1776326456970,\"responseId\":\"resp_0beebb82725bec5a0169e09738bde881918e8e24991f9bddf5\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"fd97da5f\",\"parentId\":\"cb88eb11\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-16T08:03:05.385Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Thu 2026-04-16 08:03 UTC] perfect, let's run both. you may also run the git push although i believe it does not change anything at this point. if you deem it useful i am able to provide the current docker-compose.yaml in order to have an idea of what we have built so far\"}],\"timestamp\":1776326585382}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"ef9cdd64\",\"parentId\":\"fd97da5f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-16T08:03:09.534Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_Zf5s3xdsoC2vWkbT433L6YYa|fc_0beebb82725bec5a0169e097bc41ec819193488a63f6250b90\",\"name\":\"update_plan\",\"arguments\":{\"explanation\":\"Proceeding with both refinement/canonicalization and initial timeline generation, plus preparing the repo for commit if possible.\",\"plan\":[{\"step\":\"Refine project classification and choose canonical copies for duplicates\",\"status\":\"in_progress\"},{\"step\":\"Generate initial Apollo and Aurelius timeline documents\",\"status\":\"pending\"},{\"step\":\"Commit changes and summarize outputs, noting any remaining inputs needed\",\"status\":\"pending\"}]},\"partialJson\":\"{\\\"explanation\\\":\\\"Proceeding with both refinement/canonicalization and initial timeline generation, plus preparing the repo for commit if possible.\\\",\\\"plan\\\":[{\\\"step\\\":\\\"Refine project classification and choose canonical copies for duplicates\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"in_progress\\\"},{\\\"step\\\":\\\"Generate initial Apollo and Aurelius timeline documents\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"},{\\\"step\\\":\\\"Commit changes and summarize outputs, noting any remaining inputs needed\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"pending\\\"}]}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"usage\":{\"input\":288,\"output\":94,\"cacheRead\":46336,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":46718,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.00072,\"output\":0.00141,\"cacheRead\":0.011583999999999999,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.013713999999999999}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1776326585395,\"responseId\":\"resp_0beebb82725bec5a0169e097b98eb08191bf72f1495417a190\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"cb7004f3\",\"parentId\":\"ef9cdd64\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-16T08:03:09.554Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_Zf5s3xdsoC2vWkbT433L6YYa|fc_0beebb82725bec5a0169e097bc41ec819193488a63f6250b90\",\"toolName\":\"update_plan\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Plan updated.\"}],\"details\":{\"status\":\"updated\",\"explanation\":\"Proceeding with both refinement/canonicalization and initial timeline generation, plus preparing the repo for commit if possible.\",\"plan\":[{\"step\":\"Refine project classification and choose canonical copies for duplicates\",\"status\":\"in_progress\"},{\"step\":\"Generate initial Apollo and Aurelius timeline documents\",\"status\":\"pending\"},{\"step\":\"Commit changes and summarize outputs, noting any remaining inputs needed\",\"status\":\"pending\"}]},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1776326589551}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"4ef7085d\",\"parentId\":\"cb7004f3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-16T08:03:35.038Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I’ll do both now. And yes, having the current `docker-compose.yaml` would be genuinely useful afterward, especially for connecting the project docs to the actual running stack.\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0beebb82725bec5a0169e097be916881918ef70b1765ef8826\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"commentary\\\"}\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_mv8Z8svpSGgiD0ycRt12RJAn|fc_0beebb82725bec5a0169e097bf76a08191a0694ec59f03995d\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"python3 - <<'PY'\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nimport hashlib, json, re, shutil\\nfrom collections import defaultdict\\n\\nraw = Path('/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/raw')\\nclean = Path('/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/Clean')\\nprojects_base = clean / 'projects'\\nreports = clean / 'reports'\\nreports.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n\\nfiles = sorted([p for p in raw.iterdir() if p.is_file()])\\n\\ndef sha256(p):\\n    h=hashlib.sha256()\\n    with p.open('rb') as f:\\n        for chunk in iter(lambda:f.read(1024*1024), b''):\\n            h.update(chunk)\\n    return h.hexdigest()\\n\\ndef norm_stem(name):\\n    stem=Path(name).stem.lower()\\n    stem=re.sub(r'[-_ ]+[0-9a-f]{8,}$', '', stem).strip()\\n    stem=re.sub(r'\\\\s+', ' ', stem)\\n    return stem\\n\\ndef classify(name):\\n    n=name.lower()\\n    aurelius = [r'\\\\baurelius\\\\b', r'\\\\bhfmp\\\\b', r'post-finasteride', r'post-androgen', r'pfs', r'pssd', r'androgen', r'pelvic floor', r'photobiomodulation', r'neuroendocrine', r'metabolic', r'erectile', r'bh4', r'pterin', r'proviron', r'mesterolone', r'peptide', r'red light', r'bioelectric', r'turnbuckle']\\n    apollo = [r'\\\\bapollo\\\\b', r'project apollo', r'openclaw', r'lightrag', r'crawl4ai', r'vault', r'architectur', r'knowledge engine', r'mcp', r'ollama', r'open webui', r'prior art', r'janua', r'convergence of cognition']\\n    if any(re.search(p, n) for p in aurelius):\\n        return 'aurelius'\\n    if any(re.search(p, n) for p in apollo):\\n        return 'apollo'\\n    if n == 'myactivity.html':\\n        return 'shared'\\n    return 'other'\\n\\ncanonical_by_sha = {}\\nsha_groups = defaultdict(list)\\nrecords=[]\\nfor f in files:\\n    sha = sha256(f)\\n    sha_groups[sha].append(f)\\n\\nfor sha, group in sha_groups.items():\\n    preferred = sorted(group, key=lambda p: (-len(p.name), p.name.lower()))[0]\\n    canonical_by_sha[sha] = preferred.name\\n\\nfor folder in ['apollo','aurelius','other','shared']:\\n    (projects_base / folder / 'sources').mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n\\nfor f in files:\\n    sha = sha256(f)\\n    project = classify(f.name)\\n    canonical = canonical_by_sha[sha]\\n    is_canonical = (f.name == canonical)\\n    if is_canonical:\\n        dest = projects_base / project / 'sources' / f.name\\n        if not dest.exists():\\n            shutil.copy2(f, dest)\\n    records.append({\\n        'file': f.name,\\n        'project': project,\\n        'sha256': sha,\\n        'canonical_file': canonical,\\n        'is_canonical': is_canonical,\\n        'normalized_stem': norm_stem(f.name),\\n    })\\n\\n(projects_base / 'classification_refined.json').write_text(json.dumps(records, indent=2), encoding='utf-8')\\n\\nmd=[]\\nmd.append('# Canonical Corpus Report')\\nmd.append('')\\nfor proj in ['apollo','aurelius','shared','other']:\\n    proj_records=[r for r in records if r['project']==proj]\\n    canon=[r for r in proj_records if r['is_canonical']]\\n    md.append(f'## {proj.title()}')\\n    md.append('')\\n    md.append(f'- Total assigned files: {len(proj_records)}')\\n    md.append(f'- Canonical files kept for ingestion: {len(canon)}')\\n    md.append('')\\n    for r in sorted(canon, key=lambda x:x['file'].lower()):\\n        md.append(f'  - `{r[\\\"file\\\"]}`')\\n    md.append('')\\n\\nmd.append('## Suppressed duplicates')\\nmd.append('')\\nfor sha, group in sorted(sha_groups.items(), key=lambda kv: len(kv[1]), reverse=True):\\n    if len(group) < 2:\\n        continue\\n    md.append(f'- Canonical: `{canonical_by_sha[sha]}`')\\n    for g in sorted(group, key=lambda p:p.name.lower()):\\n        if g.name != canonical_by_sha[sha]:\\n            md.append(f'  - Suppressed duplicate: `{g.name}`')\\n    md.append('')\\n\\n(reports / 'canonical_corpus_report.md').write_text('\\\\n'.join(md), encoding='utf-8')\\nprint('wrote', projects_base / 'classification_refined.json')\\nprint('wrote', reports / 'canonical_corpus_report.md')\\nfor proj in ['apollo','aurelius','shared','other']:\\n    kept = len([r for r in records if r['project']==proj and r['is_canonical']])\\n    print(proj, kept)\\nPY\",\"workdir\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":120},\"partialJson\":\"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"python3 - <<'PY'\\\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\\\nimport hashlib, json, re, shutil\\\\nfrom collections import defaultdict\\\\n\\\\nraw = Path('/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/raw')\\\\nclean = Path('/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/Clean')\\\\nprojects_base = clean / 'projects'\\\\nreports = clean / 'reports'\\\\nreports.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\\\n\\\\nfiles = sorted([p for p in raw.iterdir() if p.is_file()])\\\\n\\\\ndef sha256(p):\\\\n    h=hashlib.sha256()\\\\n    with p.open('rb') as f:\\\\n        for chunk in iter(lambda:f.read(1024*1024), b''):\\\\n            h.update(chunk)\\\\n    return h.hexdigest()\\\\n\\\\ndef norm_stem(name):\\\\n    stem=Path(name).stem.lower()\\\\n    stem=re.sub(r'[-_ ]+[0-9a-f]{8,}$', '', stem).strip()\\\\n    stem=re.sub(r'\\\\\\\\s+', ' ', stem)\\\\n    return stem\\\\n\\\\ndef classify(name):\\\\n    n=name.lower()\\\\n    aurelius = [r'\\\\\\\\baurelius\\\\\\\\b', r'\\\\\\\\bhfmp\\\\\\\\b', r'post-finasteride', r'post-androgen', r'pfs', r'pssd', r'androgen', r'pelvic floor', r'photobiomodulation', r'neuroendocrine', r'metabolic', r'erectile', r'bh4', r'pterin', r'proviron', r'mesterolone', r'peptide', r'red light', r'bioelectric', r'turnbuckle']\\\\n    apollo = [r'\\\\\\\\b