ied and suppressed logically\\n- project buckets are much cleaner\\n- Apollo and Aurelius both have timeline docs that combine:\\n  - canonical source files\\n  - conversation-derived entries from your Gemini export\\n\\nA couple of rough edges I noticed:\\n- the timeline generation is useful already, but still broad-brush\\n- some timeline docs currently include duplicated source references in the listing because the timeline builder read from project assignment plus conversation matching separately\\n- that’s fixable in the next cleanup pass\\n\\nAbout git:\\n- I did run the safe-directory config\\n- commit still failed because git user identity is not configured on this machine\\n\\nCurrent blocker for commit:\\n- `git config --global user.name \\\"...\\\"`\\n- `git config --global user.email \\\"...\\\"`\\n\\nI did **not** invent values for those.\\n\\nMy recommendation for next step:\\n1. **normalize the timelines**\\n   - remove duplicate source references\\n   - tighten project matching\\n   - split timelines into cleaner sections\\n\\n2. **generate operational docs**\\n   For Apollo and Aurelius:\\n   - `master_context.md`\\n   - `decisions.md`\\n   - `tasks.md`\\n   - `deliverables.md`\\n\\n3. **prepare LightRAG ingestion pack**\\n   - canonical sources only\\n   - project summaries included\\n\\nAnd yes, please send the current `docker-compose.yaml`.\\nThat will help me align:\\n- what services actually exist\\n- where LightRAG expects inputs\\n- what ingestion path we should automate next\\n\\nIf you want, I can start on step 2 right after you provide the compose file.\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0beebb82725bec5a0169e097f7ed808191b7625ea80e1ac136\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"usage\":{\"input\":179,\"output\":476,\"cacheRead\":53888,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":54543,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.00044750000000000004,\"output\":0.00