e\":\"edit\",\"arguments\":{\"path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"## Memory\\n\\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Project Control: Apollo\\n\\nWhen the user is working on **Project Apollo**, treat `projects/apollo/` as the canonical control folder.\\n\\n### Read before major Apollo work\\n- `projects/apollo/README.md`\\n- `projects/apollo/charter.md`\\n- `projects/apollo/status.md`\\n- `projects/apollo/checklist.md`\\n- `projects/apollo/decisions.md`\\n- `projects/apollo/handoff.md`\\n\\n### Update after meaningful Apollo progress\\nAt minimum, update:\\n- `projects/apollo/status.md`\\n- `projects/apollo/decisions.md`\\n- `projects/apollo/checklist.md`\\n- `projects/apollo/status.json`\\n\\nFor bigger shifts, also update:\\n- `projects/apollo/charter.md`\\n- `projects/apollo/roadmap.md`\\n- `projects/apollo/deliverables.md`\\n\\n### Apollo knowledge layering\\n- `projects/apollo/` = canonical control and continuity layer\\n- `Vault/Clean/` = curated corpus / evidence layer\\n- `Vault/raw/` = raw archive / evidence layer\\n\\nDo not rely on chat memory alone for Apollo continuity. Keep the files current.\\n\\n## Memory\\n\\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\\n\"}]},\"partialJson\":\"{\\\"path\\\":\\\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md\\\",\\\"edits\\\":[{\\\"oldText\\\":\\\"## Memory\\\\n\\\\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\\\\n\\\",\\\"newText\\\":\\\"## Project Control: Apollo\\\\n\\\\nWhen the user is working on **Project Apollo**, treat `projects/apollo/` as the canonical control folder.\\\\n\\\\n### Read before major Apollo work\\\\n- `projects/apollo/README.md`\\\\n- `projects/apollo/charter.md`\\\\n- `projects/apollo/status.md`\\\\n- `projects/apollo/checklist.md`\\\\n- `projects/apollo/decisions.md`\\\\n- `projects/apollo/handoff.md`\\\\n\\\\n### Update after meaningful Apollo progress\\\\nAt minimum, update:\\\\n- `projects/apollo/status.md`\\\\n- `projects/apollo/decisions.md`\\\\n- `projects/apollo/checklist.md`\\\\n- `projects/apollo/status.json`\\\\n\\\\nFor bigger shifts, also update:\\\\n- `projects/apollo/charter.md`\\\\n- `projects/apollo/roadmap.md`\\\\n- `projects/apollo/deliverables.md`\\\\n\\\\n### Apollo knowledge layering\\\\n- `projects/apollo/` = canonical control and continuity layer\\\\n- `Vault/Clean/` = curated corpus / evidence layer\\\\n- `Vault/raw/` = raw archive / evidence layer\\\\n\\\\nDo not rely on chat memory alone for Apollo continuity. Keep the files current.\\\\n\\\\n## Memory\\\\n\\\\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\\\\n\\\"}]}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"usage\":{\"input\":526,\"output\":601,\"cacheRead\":83968,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":85095,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.0013150000000000002,\"output\":0.009015,\"cacheRead\":0.020992,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.031322}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1776372305189,\"responseId\":\"resp_0143781879c152dd0169e14a5245c08191a9d187258b9db89b\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"ad6da39b\",\"parentId\":\"ae8086cf\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-16T20:45:17.641Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_0jB9XTxqP0pIsS8qa7VLRUkJ|fc_0143781879c152dd0169e14a59a2888191bfeb0e3b5417762d\",\"toolName\":\"edit\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md.\"}],\"details\":{\"diff\":\"     ...\\n  16 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\\n  17 \\n  18 Don't ask permission. Just do it.\\n  19 \\n+ 20 ## Project Control: Apollo\\n+ 21 \\n+ 22 When the user is working on **Project Apollo**, treat `projects/apollo/` as the canonical control folder.\\n+ 23 \\n+ 24 ### Read before major Apollo work\\n+ 25 - `projects/apollo/README.md`\\n+ 26 - `projects/apollo/charter.md`\\n+ 27 - `projects/apollo/status.md`\\n+ 28 - `projects/apollo/checklist.md`\\n+ 29 - `projects/apollo/decisions.md`\\n+ 30 - `projects/apollo/handoff.md`\\n+ 31 \\n+ 32 ### Update after meaningful Apollo progress\\n+ 33 At minimum, update:\\n+ 34 - `projects/apollo/status.md`\\n+ 35 - `projects/apollo/decisions.md`\\n+ 36 - `projects/apollo/checklist.md`\\n+ 37 - `projects/apollo/status.json`\\n+ 38 \\n+ 39 For bigger shifts, also update:\\n+ 40 - `projects/apollo/charter.md`\\n+ 41 - `projects/apollo/roadmap.md`\\n+ 42 - `projects/apollo/deliverables.md`\\n+ 43 \\n+ 44 ### Apollo knowledge layering\\n+ 45 - `projects/apollo/` = canonical control and continuity layer\\n+ 46 - `Vault/Clean/` = curated corpus / evidence layer\\n+ 47 - `Vault/raw/` = raw archive / evidence layer\\n+ 48 \\n+ 49 Do not rely on chat memory alone for Apollo continuity. Keep the files current.\\n+ 50 \\n  20 ## Memory\\n  21 \\n  22 You wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\\n  23 \\n     ...\",\"firstChangedLine\":20},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1776372317633}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"fb697217\",\"parentId\":\"ad6da39b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-16T20:45:24.809Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Done.\\n\\nI added an **Apollo operating rule** to `AGENTS.md` that tells future OpenClaw sessions to:\\n\\n- treat `projects/apollo/` as the canonical control folder\\n- read the key Apollo docs before major Apollo work\\n- update the key status/decision/checklist files after meaningful progress\\n- keep the layering clear between:\\n  - `projects/apollo/`\\n  - `Vault/Clean/`\\n  - `Vault/raw/`\\n\\nThis is the right kind of “programming it into the instance”, light but durable.\\n\\nIf you want, next I can inspect the current `AGENTS.md` plus the Apollo control files together and make sure the operating instructions are fully aligned.\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0143781879c152dd0169e14a6178a48191a9de0ad98790d007\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"usage\":{\"input\":135,\"output\":147,\"cacheRead\":84992,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":85274,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.0003375,\"output\":0.002205,\"cacheRead\":0.021248,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.0237905}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1776372317644,\"responseId\":\"resp_0143781879c152dd0169e14a5eca1c8191a564e93b9b153ccc\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"b28e05b4\",\"parentId\":\"fb697217\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-16T20:46:37.296Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Thu 2026-04-16 20:46 UTC] GO back to the previous answers in the chat. let us get focus back on the actual project development work. what is our next step? i do not mean actual ingestion, but conceptually\"}],\"timestamp\":1776372397291}}\n\n⚠️ [... middle content omitted — showing head and tail ...]\n\nt this isn't about actual ingestion but more about conceptual understanding. So, I think we should work on defining Apollo's first operational proof and distinguishing between control documents and the corpus. Perhaps I could phrase it as creating the \\\\\\\"first retrieval surface\\\\\\\" and developing an \\\\\\\"epistemic contract\\\\\\\" for Phase I Alpha. There are three key questions to settle as well.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Clarifying project dialogue**\\\\n\\\\nI think I should mention that we're not quite at the ingestion stage yet. Conceptually, it’s really about \\\\\\\"closing the loop from the project corpus to grounded admin dialogue.\\\\\\\" This is important because it helps frame our ongoing conversation and clarifies where we are in the process. Ultimately, the goal is to communicate clearly and effectively, so I want to ensure the user feels engaged and understands the context better.\\\"}]}\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Yes. Conceptually, our next step is **not more architecture** and **not ingestion yet**.\\n\\nIt is this:\\n\\n## Define Apollo’s first proof of usefulness\\n\\nIn plain terms:\\n\\n**What exact kind of thing must Apollo be able to know and do first, before we expand it?**\\n\\nI think the answer is:\\n\\n**Apollo’s first proof is grounded project cognition over its own planning corpus.**\\n\\nMeaning, before Aurelius operations, RV, automation, or agent orchestration, Apollo must be able to:\\n\\n- know what Apollo is for\\n- know what has been decided\\n- know what phase it is in\\n- know what the next steps are\\n- answer those questions from curated sources, not improvisation\\n\\n## So the conceptual next step is:\\n\\n# Freeze the Phase I Alpha knowledge contract\\n\\nThat means deciding, explicitly:\\n\\n### 1. What is Apollo allowed to treat as authoritative right now?\\nFor example:\\n- `projects/apollo/` as control truth\\n- selected `Vault/Clean/` files as supporting corpus\\n- `Vault/raw/` as deeper evidence only\\n\\n### 2. What questions must Apollo answer reliably?\\nFor example:\\n- What is Apollo’s mission?\\n- What is in scope now?\\n- What is deferred?\\n- What is Aurelius in relation to Apollo?\\n- What are the next build steps?\\n\\n### 3. What counts as success?\\nNot “the system exists,” but:\\n- it returns grounded answers\\n- it distinguishes decision from speculation\\n- it maintains project continuity across sessions\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Why this is the next step\\n\\nBecause we already have:\\n- the vision\\n- the architecture philosophy\\n- the roadmap\\n- the control folder\\n\\nWhat we need now is the **first bounded cognitive contract**.\\n\\nWithout that, development drifts.\\nWith it, every technical decision becomes easier.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Put even more sharply\\n\\nThe next step is:\\n\\n**decide what Apollo must be able to remember, answer, and preserve before it tries to assist, recommend, or orchestrate.**\\n\\nThat is the bridge from concept to development.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## If I phrase it as one sentence\\n\\n**Our next conceptual step is to define Apollo’s initial authoritative knowledge surface and its first set of canonical questions, so Phase I has a precise target.**\\n\\nAfter that, the technical work becomes much more straightforward.\\n\\nIf you want, I can turn that immediately into a concrete artifact:\\n\\n## “Apollo Phase I Alpha Knowledge Contract”\\nA short document defining:\\n- authoritative sources\\n- allowed retrieval surface\\n- canonical questions\\n- success criteria\\n- anti-drift rules\\n\\nThat is, in my opinion, the exact right next step.\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0143781879c152dd0169e14abbd0188191a9c2f50cc358d35e\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"usage\":{\"input\":1881,\"output\":758,\"cacheRead\":85120,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":87759,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.0047025,\"output\":0.01137,\"cacheRead\":0.02128,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.0373525}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1776372403464,\"responseId\":\"resp_0143781879c152dd0169e14ab4ab808191b789c54061240aca\"}}\n\n⚠️ [Content truncated during persistence — original exceeded size limit. Use offset/limit parameters or request specific sections for large content.]"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":101,"aggregated":"===== 1a21 tail =====\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"5e8ce264\",\"parentId\":\"dd0fd6ce\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-16T20:43:20.243Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_9ugsr0o0NCzy8XrrNlG8uVEX|fc_0143781879c152dd0169e149e833a481919d3b1234c32c42f5\",\"toolName\":\"write\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Successfully wrote 1948 bytes to /home/node/.openclaw/workspac