{"type":"message","id":"b413d607","parentId":"8f6e7230","timestamp":"2026-04-17T06:37:59.890Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes. I found **4 transcript files of interest** there, plus one `.lock` file which is not useful.\n\n## 1) `5c3a7f85-0d14-4d10-a540-96977da5f241.jsonl`\nThis is **the current session**.\n\nLast interactions:\n- I confirmed your new `AGENTS.md` backup rule was integrated\n- I created `legacy/Backups/` and backed up:\n  - `docker-compose.yaml`\n  - `apollo_up.bat`\n  - `apollo_down.bat`\n  - `.env`\n  - `AGENTS.md`\n- You then asked whether chat/session contents were also covered by a backup rule\n- I answered that transcripts are stored under `Intel/agents/main/sessions/`, but I did **not** see an explicit backup rule for them yet\n- Then you asked me to inspect the transcripts for recovery\n\nSo this file is basically our **current recovery/hardening conversation**.\n\n---\n\n## 2) `6eda9e5b-e43c-4e1d-9b5f-caf6e072e2d6.jsonl`\nThis looks like the **main Apollo conceptual discussion thread**.\n\nLast visible interactions:\n- You said you wanted a **high-level analysis of the plan**, focusing on **Apollo as a system**, not yet on the projects it will work on\n- I split off a conceptual branch so the technical thread would stay clean\n- The returned conceptual result framed Apollo as:\n  - a governed cognition/action system\n  - not just “OpenClaw + LightRAG + WebUI glued together”\n- I summarized the architecture stance:\n  - OpenClaw = orchestrator\n  - LightRAG = knowledge substrate\n  - Open WebUI = human-facing surface\n  - local models = default\n  - cloud models = escalation path\n- I ended by suggesting the next move could be turning that into a **reference architecture**\n\nSo this one is the **system-philosophy / conceptual architecture session**.\n\n---\n\n## 3) `1a218bee-b0ee-4a58-8724-239ef5ecf788.jsonl.reset.2026-04-17T04-01-07.400Z`\nThis is a **reset snapshot of an older main session**, likely one of the sessions lost/reset during the transition.\n\nLast interactions:\n- I told you the `projects/apollo/` control folder was now complete\n- I listed the created files:\n  - `README.md`\n  - `charter.md`\n  - `status.md`\n  - `decisions.md`\n  - `deliverables.md`\n  - `checklist.md`\n  - `roadmap.md`\n  - `architecture.md`\n  - `handoff.md`\n  - `sources.md`\n  - `status.json`\n- You asked whether this could be “programmed into the LLM instance” inside OpenClaw\n- I recommended **not** stuffing the whole project into the mission, but instead adding a lightweight permanent rule to `AGENTS.md`\n- You said “please do”\n- I edited `AGENTS.md` to make `projects/apollo/` the canonical project control folder\n- Then you asked:\n  - “GO back to the previous answers in the chat... what is our next step? not actual ingestion, but conceptually”\n\nSo this file preserves the phase where we:\n- **created the Apollo control layer**\n- then **wired Apollo rules into AGENTS.md**\n\nThis is probably one of the more important recovered sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 4) `95ab2a64-b730-4d1a-b975-fbff48fab4e2.jsonl.reset.2026-04-16T08-08-02.405Z`\nThis is the **earlier ingestion / LightRAG preparation session**.\n\nFrom the recovered content and prior archive note, its late-stage interactions were about:\n- refining corpus classification\n- generating Apollo and Aurelius timelines\n- creating/refining:\n  - classification outputs\n  - duplicate reports\n  - project timelines\n- trying to commit the results with git\n- hitting git problems:\n  - `safe.directory`\n  - then missing `user.name` / `user.email`\n\nThis appears to be the session where we did a lot of the **corpus preparation and project bucketing work** for Apollo/Aurelius.\n\n---\n\n## Best recovery takeaway\n\nThe most useful recovered sessions are:\n\n1. **`95ab...reset...`**\n   - corpus prep\n   - classification\n   - dedupe\n   - timeline generation\n\n2. **`1a21...reset...`**\n   - creation of `projects/apollo/`\n   - decision to make it canonical\n   - programming Apollo workflow into `AGENTS.md`\n\n3. **`6eda...jsonl`**\n   - high-level conceptual definition of Apollo as a system\n\n4. **`5c3a...jsonl`**\n   - current continuity / backup / recovery work\n\n## Important caveat\nI do **not** currently see a clean transcript of the tiny lost fragment:\n- “ok lets proceed to definig contract then”\n\nSo that exact mini-thread may not have been meaningfully preserved, or it may have been overwritten by the reset boundary.\n\nIf you want, next I can do either:\n\n1. **extract these sessions into a clean recovery note**\n2. **back up the session transcripts into `legacy/Backups/sessions/`**\n3. **search deeper inside the reset files for a specific missing exchange**","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d534c264819197686eef893427bb\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":844,"output":1162,"cacheRead":131968,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133974,"cost":{"input":0.0021100000000000003,"output":0.01743,"cacheRead":0.032992,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.052532}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776407857650,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d5321f2c8191b86f27e222f00f6f"}}
