{"type":"message","id":"3acf73d5","parentId":"6d255491","timestamp":"2026-04-17T06:46:28.988Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating session management**\n\nI need to clarify if the sessions list is current, omitting resets. It seems I'll inspect sessions.json for two active sessions. The user might ask about recovery options, and while I think using memory_search could help, it may not be necessary for this case. I'll look into the session files and metadata naming to find whether they are reset snapshots. I could also check the documentation for session management to guide me better.\n\n**Assessing recovery options**\n\nI need to determine if recovery of sessions is possible. I could suggest that while transcripts might be recoverable, active sessions may not be unless registry entries are recreated or renamed. I'll check for any session metadata in filenames or sessions.json. It might also be a good idea to consider creating backups and possibly writing a helper to restore archived files. However, the user is asking about recovery, so I'll need to explain the options clearly and inspect relevant documentation.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d73bf61881919ba8d98ae52fa8c5\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp4ddE4Y1H89yYY3Pos_D-cry-zJSfdYDS4yH9zvn5q8za7517VAcnPUCkyWcEshbCIdnX9_17kAT4VoIeZ1FQrC-xgS-_-FOkVaAFCAA4vWz97Tm1HjoNecubiG8M9P66MQxBgdVjs3UkWzqTLagerM8Jm6Ze3BSY0Ad3zoSzvWGJl_xBiQ-mhQj83c_1qOead1RCVBbfALBbiHwX9V_wrvmUo59mG88p6n7AZPhF_mNyLnIfI76GORtkgOoaEJFHdw2hoGf2qjs6iiP3FweM8qh2wP7i9uNze8zDkeedQv1STItWGKx8WIU3qvK_7-zAmJH5LlG3yz_4qETDzENc8nOMRVhVkxHIf8ythZEyc5tGl71n02vWW7O-01GV5xJsWZ4-Y-THA3VdV3dJB0iSoer1b05UjQjX4DO9X1S2H0gTbAs3aTxuYqWzOUpT_KL6LO0zh6Rz3fgfQh3xidKmAS4OORwruT3rSYZU7_rw6Jd12uFyXAOv_Fs61yVF55b0c2pXkSORG92tEtWdZeqjckuBs6hFfPDpaQdgzOzZ5NKrNZjDpE3V9-05sjdDa7OaRgvInJGslLNq1D7B4yZYdVX69gCrOm6Jk6xvZ1aoJ1B6d-qwn7zOzthgkc2N3xKIApJnfTqdLRjnF02ajGxRIzt3jZQkMNE_AZjl3Z-