2Kg=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering n8n configuration**\\n\\nI found an existing n8n encryption key, so I can add it to the .env while preserving what's there. I may need to patch the docker-compose file with health checks and consider moving secrets. The existing n8n_db service has an inline password that we'll want to change to an environment variable. Even if n8n_db isn't used right now, adding a health check might still be beneficial. However, since n8n isn’t set to use Postgres, it’s perhaps best to remove the depends_on entirely to avoid unnecessary dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing service dependencies**\\n\\nI’m thinking that while the user might rely on the database service being up, it’s currently unused. To minimize changes in behavior, I might consider keeping the depends_on as simple. However, requiring the database to be healthy before n8n starts could introduce unnecessary failure points. It could make sense to switch the DB or simply leave the depends_on as a straightforward list. Since the user requested hardening, I’ll make sure to add health checks to various services while keeping the configuration clean and minimal.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering compose file structure**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether to use a mapping style for the compose file or just keep it as a simple list. Using a condition like service_started could help preserve the existing behavior without adding unnecessary gating. However, it feels a bit odd if n8n doesn’t actually need the database. So, I’ll likely go with the service_started condition for a balanced approach while keeping things straightforward. I just want to ensure everything operates efficiently for the user!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating environment configuration**\\n\\nI'm looking into moving the POSTGRES_PASSWORD and WEBUI_SECRET_KEY to the .env file, since GATEWAY_TOKEN is already there. Should I add an N8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY environment variable too? If the current n8n config has an encryption key, it should match, so that seems good for clarity. For healthchecks, CMD-SHELL looks simpler, but I'll need to confirm shell compatibility for different images, using python where appropriate. Preserving line endings might be necessary too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering file modifications**\\n\\nI'm checking if the files might be using CRLF. If docker-compose shows CRLF, the editing tool can manage it. Since the file is only 138 lines, I could rewrite the entire content, including the necessary comments while maintaining port exposure. I need to ensure N8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY is included, but since we're not using POSTGRES_PASSWORD with n8n, should I set it anyway? The n8n_db service does use it, so I'll add it to .env. I’ll ensure to mention that the encryption key is preserved.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing update tasks**\\n\\nI think I should back up the .env and docker-compose since that’s already done. After making the modifications, maybe I should also update the daily note and Apollo status documents. It would make sense to reflect the environment hardening progress in the projects/apollo/status/checklist/decisions/status.json. However, I realize the user didn't specifically request this, so maybe I should prioritize based on their needs.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Determining n8n setup**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether the n8n image has an executable node. I believe it does. I could use bash or Node for this. I also want to add a ‘depends_on’ condition for the n8n_db to ensure it stays healthy, but it shouldn’t gate the process just yet. I’ll include comments to clarify that I’m keeping the current local n8n storage layout for now, as I plan for future use and migration. It seems like a solid plan!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Xh16RWJuUFi5Ogwb6e2uQZIz|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d8b36bd481918b701b26fa4b2481","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"docker-compose.yaml","content":"services:\n  # =========================================================\n  # 1. THE INFERENCE ENGINE\n  # =========================================================\n  ollama:\n    image: ollama/ollama:latest\n    container_name: ollama\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 60s\n    ports:\n      - \"11434:11434\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"./data/ollama:/root/.ollama\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Intel:/root/apollo_intel\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault:/root/apollo_vault\"\n    environment:\n      OLLAMA_FLASH_ATTENTION: \"1\"\n      OLLAMA_KV_CACHE_TYPE: \"q4_0\"\n      OLLAMA_NUM_GPU: \"-1\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD-SHELL\n        - ollama list >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 1\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 60s\n    deploy:\n      resources:\n        reservations:\n          devices:\n            - driver: nvidia\n              count: all\n              capabilities: [\"gpu\"]\n\n  # =========================================================\n  # 2. THE LIBRARIAN\n  # =========================================================\n  apollo-agent:\n    image: ghcr.io/openclaw/openclaw:latest\n    container_name: apollo-agent\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 45s\n    ports:\n      - \"18789:18789\"\n    environment:\n      OLLAMA_BASE_URL: \"http://ollama:11434\"\n      OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT: \"18789\"\n      ALLOW_FILE_MODIFICATION: \"true\"\n      ALLOW_DESKTOP_INTERACTION: \"true\"\n      WORKSPACE_DIR: \"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace\"\n      GATEWAY_TOKEN: \"${APOLLO_TOKEN}\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Intel:/home/node/.openclaw\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace\"\n      # Compatibility aliases for old paths already used in-session.\n      # Keep for now, remove later once path usage is normalized.\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Raw:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/raw\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Clean:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/clean\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Database:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/database\"\n    depends_on:\n      ollama:\n        condition: service_healthy\n    command: [\"node\", \"dist/index.js\", \"gateway\"]\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - node\n        - -e\n        - |\n          const net=require('net');\n          const s=net.connect({host:'127.0.0.1',port:18789},()=>{s.end();process.exit(0)});\n          s.on('error',()=>process.exit(1));\n          setTimeout(()=>process.exit(1),3000);\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 45s\n\n  # =========================================================\n  # 3. THE PURIFIER\n  # =========================================================\n  docling:\n    image: ghcr.io/docling-project/docling-serve:latest\n    container_name: docling\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 30s\n    ports:\n      - \"5001:5001\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Raw:/root/apollo_raw\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Clean:/root/apollo_clean\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - python\n        - -c\n        - |\n          import socket; s=socket.socket(); s.settimeout(3); s.connect((\"127.0.0.1\",5001)); s.close()\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 45s\n\n  # =========================================================\n  # 4. THE MEMORY\n  # =========================================================\n  lightrag:\n    image: ghcr.io/hkuds/lightrag:latest\n    container_name: apollo-lightrag\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 45s\n    ports:\n      - \"9621:9621\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Database:/app/data/rag_storage\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Clean:/app/data/inputs\"\n    environment:\n      LLM_BINDING: \"ollama\"\n      LLM_BINDING_HOST: \"http://ollama:11434\"\n      LLM_MODEL: \"Apollo-Architect\"\n      EMBEDDING_BINDING: \"ollama\"\n      EMBEDDING_BINDING_HOST: \"http://ollama:11434\"\n      EMBEDDING_MODEL: \"nomic-embed-text\"\n      SUMMARY_CONTEXT_SIZE: \"32000\"\n    depends_on:\n      ollama:\n        condition: service_healthy\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - python\n        - -c\n        - |\n          import socket; s=socket.socket(); s.settimeout(3); s.connect((\"127.0.0.1\",9621)); s.close()\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 60s\n\n  # =========================================================\n  # 5. THE SCOUTS\n  # =========================================================\n  browserless:\n    image: browserless/chrome:latest\n    container_name: browserless\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 30s\n    ports:\n      - \"3003:3000\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - node\n        - -e\n        - |\n          const net=require('net');\n          const s=net.connect({host:'127.0.0.1',port:3000},()=>{s.end();process.exit(0)});\n          s.on('error',()=>process.exit(1));\n          setTimeout(()=>process.exit(1),3000);\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 45s\n\n  crawl4ai:\n    image: unclecode/crawl4ai:latest\n    container_name: apollo-scout\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 30s\n    ports:\n      - \"11235:11235\"\n    environment:\n      MAX_CONCURRENT_TASKS: \"3\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - python\n        - -c\n        - |\n          import socket; s=socket.socket(); s.settimeout(3); s.connect((\"127.0.0.1\",11235)); s.close()\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 45s\n\n  # =========================================================\n  # 6. THE CONDUCTORS\n  # =========================================================\n  # Keep this database service restart-safe, but do not silently migrate n8n\n  # to Postgres in this pass. The current n8n data directory already contains\n  # a live SQLite database, and switching backends here could strand state.\n  n8n_db:\n    image: postgres:16\n    container_name: n8n_db\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 60s\n    environment:\n      POSTGRES_USER: \"apollo_admin\"\n      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: \"${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}\"\n      POSTGRES_DB: \"apollo_state\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"./data/postgres:/var/lib/postgresql/data\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD-SHELL\n        - pg_isready -U $$POSTGRES_USER -d $$POSTGRES_DB\n      interval: 20s\n      timeout: 5s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 20s\n\n  n8n:\n    image: n8nio/n8n:latest\n    container_name: n8n\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 45s\n    ports:\n      - \"5678:5678\"\n    environment:\n      N8N_HOST: \"0.0.0.0\"\n      N8N_PORT: \"5678\"\n      N8N_RUNNERS_ENABLED: \"true\"\n      # Preserve the existing credential encryption key explicitly so restart\n      # behavior is stable and credentials do not drift.\n      N8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY: \"${N8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY}\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"./data/n8n:/home/node/.n8n\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Intel:/home/node/apollo_intel\"\n    depends_on:\n      n8n_db:\n        condition: service_started\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - node\n        - -e\n        - |\n          const net=require('net');\n          const s=net.connect({host:'127.0.0.1',port:5678},()=>{s.end();process.exit(0)});\n          s.on('error',()=>process.exit(1));\n          setTimeout(()=>process.exit(1),3000);\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 60s\n\n  # =========================================================\n  # 7. THE INTERFACE\n  # =========================================================\n  open-webui:\n    image: ghcr.io/open-webui/open-webui:cuda\n    container_name: open-webui\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 45s\n    ports:\n      - \"3000:8080\"\n    environment:\n      OLLAMA_BASE_URL: \"http://ollama:11434\"\n      WEBUI_SECRET_KEY: \"${WEBUI_SECRET_KEY}\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"./data/open-webui:/app/backend/data\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Intel:/app/backend/data/apollo_intel\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo:/app/backend/data/apollo_repo\"\n    depends_on:\n      ollama:\n        condition: service_healthy\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - python\n        - -c\n        - |\n          import socket; s=socket.socket(); s.settimeout(3); s.connect((\"127.0.0.1\",8080)); s.close()\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 60s\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"docker-compose.yaml\",\"content\":\"services:\\n  # =========================================================\\n  # 1. THE INFERENCE ENGINE\\n  # =========================================================\\n  ollama:\\n    image: ollama/ollama:latest\\n    container_name: ollama\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n    init: true\\n    stop_grace_period: 60s\\n    ports:\\n      - \\\"11434:11434\\\"\\n    volumes:\\n      - \\\"./data/ollama:/root/.ollama\\\"\\n      - \\\"C:/Apollo/Intel:/root/apollo_intel\\\"\\n      - \\\"C:/Apollo/Vault:/root/apollo_vault\\\"\\n    environment:\\n      OLLAMA_FLASH_ATTENTION: \\\"1\\\"\\n      OLLAMA_KV_CACHE_TYPE: \\\"q4_0\\\"\\n      OLLAMA_NUM_GPU: \\\"-1\\\"\\n    healthcheck:\\n      test:\\n        - CMD-SHELL\\n        - ollama list >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 1\\n      interval: 30s\\n      timeout: 10s\\n      retries: 10\\n      start_period: 60s\\n    deploy:\\n      resources:\\n        reservations:\\n          devices:\\n            - driver: nvidia\\n              count: all\\n              capabili