e repo root `C:\\Apollo` is now mounted as the OpenClaw workspace root\n- The conversation is happening against the live running stack\n- A first hardening pass has now been applied to `docker-compose.yaml` and `.env`:\n  - restart policies added across services\n  - graceful stop timings added\n  - healthchecks added for core services\n  - compose-managed secrets moved into `.env`\n  - remote-exposed ports intentionally left unchanged\n  - `n8n` was **not** switched to Postgres in this pass, to avoid an implicit state migration away from the existing SQLite-backed runtime\n"},{"oldText":"## Immediate next actions\n1. inspect and validate `Vault/Clean` as the initial retrieval corpus\n2. verify what LightRAG is actually reading from `Vault/Clean`\n3. define and/or verify the indexing path for the clean corpus\n4. prove the admin query loop with canonical Apollo questions\n5. keep secrets and irrelevant runtime debris out of the retrieval surface\n","newText":"## Immediate next actions\n1. validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\n2. rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness/health rather than fixed sleeps\n3. inspect and validate `Vault/Clean` as the initial retrieval corpus\n4. verify what LightRAG is actually reading from `Vault/Clean`\n5. define and/or verify the indexing path for the clean corpus\n6. prove the admin query loop with canonical Apollo questions\n7. keep secrets and irrelevant runtime debris out of the retrieval surface\n"},{"oldText":"## Known issues / open operational concerns\n- Git inside the container currently reports a safe-directory ownership issue\n- Path naming conventions should be kept consistent (`Vault/...` rather than mixed variants in project docs/scripts)\n- Sensitive files inside the repo tree must never be ingested casually\n- The root workspace identity/memory files are still somewhat fresh and minimal after migration\n","newText":"## Known issues / open operational concerns\n- Git inside the container currently reports a safe-directory ownership issue\n- Path naming conventions should be kept consistent (`Vault/...` rather than mixed variants in project docs/scripts)\n- Sensitive files inside the repo tree must never be ingested casually\n- The root workspace identity/memory files are still somewhat fresh and minimal after migration\n- The hardened compose file still needs validation against the real Docker runtime, because Docker CLI access is not available from the current session\n- `n8n_db` exists and is restart-safe, but `n8n` is intentionally still left on the existing SQLite-backed runtime until a deliberate migration is planned\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"projects/apollo/status.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"### Runtime / platform\\n- The Docker stack is live and already includes the main Apollo building blocks:\\n  - OpenClaw\\n  - Ollama\\n  - Open WebUI\\n  - LightRAG\\n  - Docling\\n  - Browserless\\n  - Crawl4AI\\n  - n8n + Postgres\\n- The repo root `C:\\\\Apollo` is now mounted as the OpenClaw workspace root\\n- The conversation is happening against the live running stack\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Runtime / platform\\n- The Docker stack is live and already includes the main Apollo building blocks:\\n  - OpenClaw\\n  - Ollama\\n  - Open WebUI\\n  - LightRAG\\n  - Docling\\n  - Browserless\\n  - Crawl4AI\\n  - n8n + Postgres\\n- The repo root `C:\\\\Apollo` is now mounted as the OpenClaw workspace root\\n- The conversation is happening against the live running stack\\n- A first hardening pass has now been applied to `docker-compose.yaml` and `.env`:\\n  - restart policies added across services\\n  - graceful stop timings added\\n  - healthchecks added for core services\\n  - compose-managed secrets moved into `.env`\\n  - remote-exposed ports intentionally left unchanged\\n  - `n8n` was **not** switched to Postgres in this pass, to avoid an implicit state migration away from the existing SQLite-backed runtime\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"## Immediate next actions\\n1. inspect and validate `Vault/Clean` as the initial retrieval corpus\\n2. verify what LightRAG is actually reading from `Vault/Clean`\\n3. define and/or verify the indexing path for the clean corpus\\n4. prove the admin query loop with canonical Apollo questions\\n5. keep secrets and irrelevant runtime debris out of the retrieval surface\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Immediate next actions\\n1. validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\\n2. rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness/health rather than fixed sleeps\\n3. inspect and validate `Vault/Clean` as the initial retrieval corpus\\n4. verify what LightRAG is actually reading from `Vault/Clean`\\n5. define and/or verify the indexing path for the clean corpus\\n6. prove the admin query loop with canonical Apollo questions\\n7. keep secrets and irrelevant runtime debris out of the retrieval surface\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"## Known issues / open operational concerns\\n- Git inside the container currently reports a safe-directory ownership issue\\n- Path naming conventions should be kept consistent (`Vault/...` rather than mixed variants in project docs/scripts)\\n- Sensitive files inside the repo tree must never be ingested casually\\n- The root workspace identity/memory files are still somewhat fresh and minimal after migration\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Known issues / open operational concerns\\n- Git inside the container currently reports a safe-directory ownership issue\\n- Path naming conventions should be kept consistent (`Vault/...` rather than mixed variants in project docs/scripts)\\n- Sensitive files inside the repo tree must never be ingested casually\\n- The root workspace identity/memory files are still somewhat fresh and minimal after migration\\n- The hardened compose file still needs validation against the real Docker runtime, because Docker CLI access is not available from the current session\\n- `n8n_db` exists and is restart-safe, but `n8n` is intentionally still left on the existing SQLite-backed runtime until a deliberate migration is planned\\n\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_QiEKBE0EqdBBqRfbPZuQvnJg|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d9251334819187c40dc8b2857912","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"projects/apollo/checklist.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### A. Workspace and control layer\n- [x] Make repo root `C:\\Apollo` the active OpenClaw workspace root\n- [x] Expose the full repo to the running OpenClaw session\n- [x] Preserve the existing running stack as the basis\n- [x] Create canonical Apollo control docs under `projects/apollo/`\n- [ ] Add repo root as a safe Git directory inside the container if git operations are needed\n","newText":"### A. Workspace and control layer\n- [x] Make repo root `C:\\Apollo` the active OpenClaw workspace root\n- [x] Expose the full repo to the running OpenClaw session\n- [x] Preserve the existing running stack as the basis\n- [x] Create canonical Apollo control docs under `projects/apollo/`\n- [x] Back up core project/runtime files before editing them (`legacy/Backups/`)\n- [ ] Add repo root as a safe Git directory inside the container if git operations are needed\n"},{"oldText":"### B. Repo hygiene\n- [x] Archive the clearly legacy nested workspace content from `Intel/workspace/` into `legacy/`\n- [x] Preserve active OpenClaw runtime/config state under `Intel/`\n- [ ] Confirm any remaining legacy leftovers are either archived or intentionally retained\n- [ ] Document any directories that must never be ingested\n","newText":"### B. Repo hygiene\n- [x] Archive the clearly legacy nested workspace content from `Intel/workspace/` into `legacy/`\n- [x] Preserve active OpenClaw runtime/config state under `Intel/`\n- [x] Move compose-managed secrets out of `docker-compose.yaml` and into `.env`\n- [ ] Confirm any remaining legacy leftovers are either archived or intentionally retained\n- [ ] Document any directories that must never be ingested\n"},{"oldText":"### D. Retrieval validation\n- [ ] Confirm how LightRAG is currently reading `Vault/Clean`\n- [ ] Define the exact indexing / refresh path for the clean corpus\n- [ ] Verify project-scoped retrieval assumptions for Apollo vs Aurelius\n- [ ] Test the first grounded Apollo query loop\n","newText":"### D. Retrieval validation\n- [ ] Confirm how LightRAG is currently reading `Vault/Clean`\n- [ ] Define the exact indexing / refresh path for the clean corpus\n- [ ] Verify project-scoped retrieval assumptions for Apollo vs Aurelius\n- [ ] Test the first grounded Apollo query loop\n\n### F. Runtime hardening\n- [x] Add restart policies and graceful stop settings to core services in `docker-compose.yaml`\n- [x] Add core service healthchecks to `docker-compose.yaml`\n- [ ] Validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\n- [ ] Rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness / health checks\n- [ ] Plan an explicit `n8n` backend migration if Postgres should become authoritative later\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"projects/apollo/checklist.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"### A. Workspace and control layer\\n- [x] Make repo root `C:\\\\Apollo` the active OpenClaw workspace root\\n- [x] Expose the full repo to the running OpenClaw session\\n- [x] Preserve the existing running stack as the basis\\n- [x] Create canonical Apollo control docs under `projects/apollo/`\\n- [ ] Add repo root as a safe Git directory inside the container if git operations are needed\\n\",\"newText\":\"### A. Workspace and control layer\\n- [x] Make repo root `C:\\\\Apollo` the active OpenClaw workspace root\\n- [x] Expose the full repo to the running OpenClaw session\\n- [x] Preserve the existing running stack as the basis\\n- [x] Create canonical Apollo control docs under `projects/apollo/`\\n- [x] Back up core project/runtime files before editing them (`legacy/Backups/`)\\n- [ ] Add repo root as a safe Git directory inside the container if git operations are needed\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"### B. Repo hygiene\\n- [x] Archive the clearly legacy nested workspace content from `Intel/workspace/` into `legacy/`\\n- [x] Preserve active OpenClaw runtime/config state under `Intel/`\\n- [ ] Confirm any remaining legacy leftovers are either archived or intentionally retained\\n- [ ] Document any directories that must never be ingested\\n\",\"newText\":\"### B. Repo hygiene\\n- [x] Archive the clearly legacy nested workspace content from `Intel/workspace/` into `legacy/`\\n- [x] Preserve active OpenClaw runtime/config state under `Intel/`\\n- [x] Move compose-managed secrets out of `docker-compose.yaml` and into `.env`\\n- [ ] Confirm any remaining legacy leftovers are either archived or intentionally retained\\n- [ ] Document any directories that must never be ingested\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"### D. Retrieval validation\\n- [ ] Confirm how LightRAG is currently reading `Vault/Clean`\\n- [ ] Define the exact indexing / refresh path for the clean corpus\\n- [ ] Verify project-scoped retrieval assumptions for Apollo vs Aurelius\\n- [ ] Test the first grounded Apollo query loop\\n\",\"newText\":\"### D. Retrieval validation\\n- [ ] Confirm how LightRAG is currently reading `Vault/Clean`\\n- [ ] Define the exact indexing / refresh path for the clean corpus\\n- [ ] Verify project-scoped retrieval assumptions for Apollo vs Aurelius\\n- [ ] Test the first grounded Apollo query loop\\n\\n### F. Runtime hardening\\n- [x] Add restart policies and graceful stop settings to core services in `docker-compose.yaml`\\n- [x] Add core service healthchecks to `docker-compose.yaml`\\n- [ ] Validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\\n- [ ] Rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness / health checks\\n- [ ] Plan an explicit `n8n` backend migration if Postgres should become authoritative later\\n\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_A6JD3u9L0DP52iuTtSxRqR5z|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d92513408191a8347cb16a5c25b6","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"projects/apollo/decisions.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### Workspace / repo hygiene\n- The repo root `C:\\Apollo` is now the active OpenClaw workspace root\n- The legacy nested workspace under `Intel/workspace/` should be archived rather than deleted\n- Runtime/config/state under `Intel/` should be handled conservatively to avoid breaking the live system\n","newText":"### Workspace / repo hygiene\n- The repo root `C:\\Apollo` is now the active OpenClaw workspace root\n- The legacy nested workspace under `Intel/workspace/` should be archived rather than deleted\n- Runtime/config/state under `Intel/` should be handled conservatively to avoid breaking the live system\n- Before modifying core runtime/project files such as `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, and `.env`, create a dated/versioned backup under `legacy/Backups/`\n\n### Runtime hardening stance\n- Remote access is required, so current port exposure remains intentionally unchanged in this hardening pass\n- `docker-compose.yaml` should be hardened with restart policies, graceful stop periods, and healthchecks across core services\n- Compose-managed secrets should live in `.env`, not inline in `docker-compose.yaml`\n- `n8n` should remain on its current SQLite-backed runtime for now, rather than being silently migrated to Postgres during a hardening pass\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"projects/apollo/decisions.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"### Workspace / repo hygiene\\n- The repo root `C:\\\\Apollo` is now the active OpenClaw workspace root\\n- The legacy nested workspace under `Intel/workspace/` should be archived rather than deleted\\n- Runtime/config/state under `Intel/` should be handled conservatively to avoid breaking the live system\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Workspace / repo hygiene\\n- The repo root `C:\\\\Apollo` is now the active OpenClaw workspace root\\n- The legacy nested workspace under `Intel/workspace/` should be archived rather than deleted\\n- Runtime/config/state under `Intel/` should be handled conservatively to avoid breaking the live system\\n- Before modifying core runtime/project files such as `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, and `.env`, create a dated/versioned backup under `legacy/Backups/`\\n\\n### Runtime hardening stance\\n- Remote access is required, so current port exposure remains intentionally unchanged in this hardening pass\\n- `docker-compose.yaml` should be hardened with restart policies, graceful stop periods, and healthchecks across core services\\n- Compose-managed secrets should live in `.env`, not inline in `docker-compose.yaml`\\n- `n8n` should remain on its current SQLite-backed runtime for now, rather than being silently migrated to Postgres during a hardening pass\\n\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_z4hOtHw5ThGd6OclrF5iK4TU|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d925134c819192b51dd0b3b90042","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"projects/apollo/status.json","edits":[{"oldText":"  \"focus\": \"Establish a thin but real Apollo backbone using the existing running stack and the existing clean Apollo/Aurelius corpus, then prove the first grounded retrieval/query loop.\",","newText":"  \"focus\": \"Establish a thin but real Apollo backbone using the existing running stack and the existing clean Apollo/Aurelius corpus, while hardening runtime continuity enough to survive standby/restart events and then proving the first grounded retrieval/query loop.\""},{"oldText":"  \"next_actions\": [\n    \"inspect Vault/Clean ingest and classification manifests\",\n    \"verify LightRAG input and indexing behavior\",\n    \"define the first retrieval surface\",\n    \"prove the first grounded Apollo query loop\",\n    \"create a validation pack of canonical project questions\"\n  ],","newText":"  \"next_actions\": [\n    \"validate the hardened docker-compose.yaml against the live runtime\",\n    \"rewrite apollo_up.bat and apollo_down.bat around readiness and health checks\",\n    \"inspect Vault/Clean ingest and classification manifests\",\n    \"verify LightRAG input and indexing behavior\",\n    \"define the first retrieval surface\",\n    \"prove the first grounded Apollo query loop\",\n    \"create a validation pack of canonical project questions\"\n  ],"},{"oldText":"  \"blockers\": [\n    \"Git safe.directory issue inside container if repo operations are needed\",\n    \"LightRAG end-to-end indexing behavior against the clean corpus not yet verified\"\n  ],","newText":"  \"blockers\": [\n    \"Git safe.directory issue inside container if repo operations are needed\",\n    \"Live Docker validation is not available from the current session because Docker CLI access is missing here\",\n    \"LightRAG end-to-end indexing behavior against the clean corpus not yet verified\"\n  ],"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"projects/apollo/status.json\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"  \\\"focus\\\": \\\"Establish a thin but real Apollo backbone using the existing running stack and the existing clean Apollo/Aurelius corpus, then prove the first grounded retrieval/query loop.\\\",\",\"newText\":\"  \\\"focus\\\": \\\"Establish a thin but real Apollo backbone using the existing running stack and the existing clean Apollo/Aurelius corpus, while hardening runtime continuity enough to survive standby/restart events and then proving the first grounded retrieval/query loop.\\\"\"},{\"oldText\":\"  \\\"next_actions\\\": [\\n    \\\"inspect Vault/Clean ingest and classification manifests\\\",\\n    \\\"verify LightRAG input and indexing behavior\\\",\\n    \\\"define the first retrieval surface\\\",\\n    \\\"prove the first grounded Apollo query loop\\\",\\n    \\\"create a validation pack of canonical project questions\\\"\\n  ],\",\"newText\":\"  \\\"next_actions\\\": [\\n    \\\"validate the hardened docker-compose.yaml against the live runtime\\\",\\n    \\\"rewrite apollo_up.bat and apollo_down.bat around readiness and health checks\\\",\\n    \\\"inspect Vault/Clean ingest and classification manifests\\\",\\n    \\\"verify LightRAG input and indexing behavior\\\",\\n    \\\"define the first retrieval surface\\\",\\n    \\\"prove the first grounded Apollo query loop\\\",\\n    \\\"create a validation pack of canonical project questions\\\"\\n  ],\"},{\"oldText\":\"  \\\"blockers\\\": [\\n    \\\"Git safe.directory issue inside container if repo operations are needed\\\",\\n    \\\"LightRAG end-to-end indexing behavior against the clean corpus not yet verified\\\"\\n  ],\",\"newText\":\"  \\\"blockers\\\": [\\n    \\\"Git safe.directory issue inside container if repo operations are needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Live Docker validation is not available from the current session because Docker CLI access is missing here\\\",\\n    \\\"LightRAG end-to-end indexing behavior against the clean corpus not yet verified\\\"\\n  ],\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":984,"output":2598,"cacheRead":132608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":136190,"cost":{"input":0.0024600000000000004,"output":0.03897,"cacheRead":0.033152,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.074582}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776408820221,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d8f4e4388191984be600931e1892"}}
{"type":"message","id":"78b9afba","parentId":"c155750b","timestamp":"2026-04-17T06:54:29.525Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_IrbwYnEAcTFz827jtnrpk1Wc|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d925131c819199829eb945dd8d74","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 3 block(s) in projects/apollo/status.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 18   - Crawl4AI\n 19   - n8n + Postgres\n 20 - The repo root `C:\\Apollo` is now mounted as the OpenClaw workspace root\n 21 - The conversation is happening against the live running stack\n+22 - A first hardening pass has now been applied to `docker-compose.yaml` and `.env`:\n+23   - restart policies added across services\n+24   - graceful stop timings added\n+25   - healthchecks added for core services\n+26   - compose-managed secrets moved into `.env`\n+27   - remote-exposed ports intentionally left unchanged\n+28   - `n8n` was **not** switched to Postgres in this pass, to avoid an implicit state migration away from the existing SQLite-backed runtime\n 22 \n 23 ### Repository / workspace\n 24 - The full repo is now visible inside OpenClaw\n 25 - The old nested workspace under `Intel/workspace/` has been substantially sanitized and archived to `legacy/Intel/workspace/`\n    ...\n 48 2. ensure it is retrieval-ready\n 49 3. establish source-grounded querying through the running system\n 50 \n 51 ## Immediate next actions\n-52 1. inspect and validate `Vault/Clean` as the initial retrieval corpus\n-53 2. verify what LightRAG is actually reading from `Vault/Clean`\n-54 3. define and/or verify the indexing path for the clean corpus\n-55 4. prove the admin query loop with canonical Apollo questions\n-56 5. keep secrets and irrelevant runtime debris out of the retrieval surface\n+59 1. validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\n+60 2. rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness/health rather than fixed sleeps\n+61 3. inspect and validate `Vault/Clean` as the initial retrieval corpus\n+62 4. verify what LightRAG is actually reading from `Vault/Clean`\n+63 5. define and/or verify the indexing path for the clean corpus\n+64 6. prove the admin query loop with canonical Apollo questions\n+65 7. keep secrets and irrelevant runtime debris out of the retrieval surface\n 57 \n 58 ## Known issues / open operational concerns\n 59 - Git inside the container currently reports a safe-directory ownership issue\n 60 - Path naming conventions should be kept consistent (`Vault/...` rather than mixed variants in project docs/scripts)\n 61 - Sensitive files inside the repo tree must never be ingested casually\n 62 - The root workspace identity/memory files are still somewhat fresh and minimal after migration\n+72 - The hardened compose file still needs validation against the real Docker runtime, because Docker CLI access is not available from the current session\n+73 - `n8n_db` exists and is restart-safe, but `n8n` is intentionally still left on the existing SQLite-backed runtime until a deliberate migration is planned\n 63 \n 64 ## Current recommendation\n 65 Do not expand scope yet.\n 66 Use the existing cleaned corpus and the existing running stack to prove the first real Apollo capability before adding more automation.","firstChangedLine":22},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776408869516}}
{"type":"message","id":"f51d349b","parentId":"78b9afba","timestamp":"2026-04-17T06:54:29.531Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_QiEKBE0EqdBBqRfbPZuQvnJg|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d9251334819187c40dc8b2857912","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 3 block(s) in projects/apollo/checklist.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  6 - [x] Make repo root `C:\\Apollo` the active OpenClaw workspace root\n  7 - [x] Expose the full repo to the running OpenClaw session\n  8 - [x] Preserve the existing running stack as the basis\n  9 - [x] Create canonical Apollo control docs under `projects/apollo/`\n+10 - [x] Back up core project/runtime files before editing them (`legacy/Backups/`)\n 10 - [ ] Add repo root as a safe Git directory inside the container if git operations are needed\n 11 \n 12 ### B. Repo hygiene\n 13 - [x] Archive the clearly legacy nested workspace content from `Intel/workspace/` into `legacy/`\n 14 - [x] Preserve active OpenClaw runtime/config state under `Intel/`\n+16 - [x] Move compose-managed secrets out of `docker-compose.yaml` and into `.env`\n 15 - [ ] Confirm any remaining legacy leftovers are either archived or intentionally retained\n 16 - [ ] Document any directories that must never be ingested\n 17 \n 18 ### C. Corpus validation\n    ...\n 28 - [ ] Define the exact indexing / refresh path for the clean corpus\n 29 - [ ] Verify project-scoped retrieval assumptions for Apollo vs Aurelius\n 30 - [ ] Test the first grounded Apollo query loop\n 31 \n+34 ### F. Runtime hardening\n+35 - [x] Add restart policies and graceful stop settings to core services in `docker-compose.yaml`\n+36 - [x] Add core service healthchecks to `docker-compose.yaml`\n+37 - [ ] Validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\n+38 - [ ] Rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness / health checks\n+39 - [ ] Plan an explicit `n8n` backend migration if Postgres should become authoritative later\n+4