{"type":"message","id":"7296c285","parentId":"f7396c0e","timestamp":"2026-04-17T06:54:40.388Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_SHWOczvYQTLwUOM2MeEZ5RT6|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d93096bc81919d302628237fdc4f","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"memory/2026-04-17.md","edits":[{"oldText":"- The user added a new workspace rule: before modifying core project/runtime files like `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and similar files, create dated/versioned backups in `legacy/Backups/`.\n- Seeded `legacy/Backups/` with backups of `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and `AGENTS.md`, and added `scripts/backup_core_project_files.sh` to make that easier to follow consistently.\n","newText":"- The user added a new workspace rule: before modifying core project/runtime files like `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and similar files, create dated/versioned backups in `legacy/Backups/`.\n- Seeded `legacy/Backups/` with backups of `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and `AGENTS.md`, and added `scripts/backup_core_project_files.sh` to make that easier to follow consistently.\n- Backed up `docker-compose.yaml` and `.env` again as `v2` snapshots before hardening them.\n- Hardened `docker-compose.yaml` with restart policies, `init: true`, graceful stop periods, and core service healthchecks, while keeping remote-access port exposure unchanged.\n- Moved compose-managed secrets into `.env` and added `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `WEBUI_SECRET_KEY`, and the existing `N8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY` there.\n- Deliberately did **not** switch `n8n` to Postgres in this pass, to avoid silently stranding the existing SQLite-backed state.\n- Updated Apollo control docs to record the hardening decisions and next validation steps.\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"memory/2026-04-17.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"- The user added a new workspace rule: before modifying core project/runtime files like `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and similar files, create dated/versioned backups in `legacy/Backups/`.\\n- Seeded `legacy/Backups/` with backups of `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and `AGENTS.md`, and added `scripts/backup_core_project_files.sh` to make that easier to follow consistently.\\n\",\"newText\":\"- The user added a new workspace rule: before modifying core project/runtime files like `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and similar files, create dated/versioned backups in `legacy/Backups/`.\\n- Seeded `legacy/Backups/` with backups of `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and `AGENTS.md`, and added `scripts/backup_core_project_files.sh` to make that easier to follow consistently.\\n- Backed up `docker-compose.yaml` and `.env` again as `v2` snapshots before hardening them.\\n- Hardened `docker-compose.yaml` with restart policies, `init: true`, graceful stop periods, and core service healthchecks, while keeping remote-access port exposure unchanged.\\n- Moved compose-managed secrets into `.env` and added `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `WEBUI_SECRET_KEY`, and the existing `N8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY` there.\\n- Deliberately did **not** switch `n8n` to Postgres in this pass, to avoid silently stranding the existing SQLite-backed state.\\n- Updated Apollo control docs to record the hardening decisions and next validation steps.\\n\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_OWmh51ZVL4oDnV19FCEJLKKY|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d93096d08191b41267fa2fd233f0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,220p' docker-compose.yaml && printf '\\n--- .env ---\\n' && sed -n '1,20p' .env","workdir":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":20},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"sed -n '1,220p' docker-compose.yaml && printf '\\\\n--- .env ---\\\\n' && sed -n '1,20p' .env\",\"workdir\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":20}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":14479,"output":502,"cacheRead":120320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135301,"cost":{"input":0.0361975,"output":0.00753,"cacheRead":0.03008,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0738075}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776408869554,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d925d50081918b521b5e3a9f9b16"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9aa43088","parentId":"7296c285","timestamp":"2026-04-17T06:54:40.465Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_SHWOczvYQTLwUOM2MeEZ5RT6|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d93096bc81919d302628237fdc4f","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in memory/2026-04-17.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  8 - Updated `AGENTS.md` with instructions to restore `MEMORY.md` from backup if it ever goes missing again.\n  9 - Added a local `scripts/memory_backup_daemon.sh` watchdog and started it with a 10-minute interval so `MEMORY.md` is backed up automatically.\n 10 - The user added a new workspace rule: before modifying core project/runtime files like `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and similar files, create dated/versioned backups in `legacy/Backups/`.\n 11 - Seeded `legacy/Backups/` with backups of `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and `AGENTS.md`, and added `scripts/backup_core_project_files.sh` to make that easier to follow consistently.\n+12 - Backed up `docker-compose.yaml` and `.env` again as `v2` snapshots before hardening them.\n+13 - Hardened `docker-compose.yaml` with restart policies, `init: true`, graceful stop periods, and core service healthchecks, while keeping remote-access port exposure unchanged.\n+14 - Moved compose-managed secrets into `.env` and added `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `WEBUI_SECRET_KEY`, and the existing `N8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY` there.\n+15 - Deliberately did **not** switch `n8n` to Postgres in this pass, to avoid silently stranding the existing SQLite-backed state.\n+16 - Updated Apollo control docs to record the hardening decisions and next validation steps.","firstChangedLine":12},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776408880461}}
{"type":"message","id":"70b45365","parentId":"9aa43088","timestamp":"2026-04-17T06:54:40.470Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_OWmh51ZVL4oDnV19FCEJLKKY|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1d93096d08191b41267fa2fd233f0","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"services:\n  # =========================================================\n  # 1. THE INFERENCE ENGINE\n  # =========================================================\n  ollama:\n    image: ollama/ollama:latest\n    container_name: ollama\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 60s\n    ports:\n      - \"11434:11434\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"./data/ollama:/root/.ollama\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Intel:/root/apollo_intel\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault:/root/apollo_vault\"\n    environment:\n      OLLAMA_FLASH_ATTENTION: \"1\"\n      OLLAMA_KV_CACHE_TYPE: \"q4_0\"\n      OLLAMA_NUM_GPU: \"-1\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD-SHELL\n        - ollama list >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 1\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 60s\n    deploy:\n      resources:\n        reservations:\n          devices:\n            - driver: nvidia\n              count: all\n              capabilities: [\"gpu\"]\n\n  # =========================================================\n  # 2. THE LIBRARIAN\n  # =========================================================\n  apollo-agent:\n    image: ghcr.io/openclaw/openclaw:latest\n    container_name: apollo-agent\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 45s\n    ports:\n      - \"18789:18789\"\n    environment:\n      OLLAMA_BASE_URL: \"http://ollama:11434\"\n      OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT: \"18789\"\n      ALLOW_FILE_MODIFICATION: \"true\"\n      ALLOW_DESKTOP_INTERACTION: \"true\"\n      WORKSPACE_DIR: \"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace\"\n      GATEWAY_TOKEN: \"${APOLLO_TOKEN}\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Intel:/home/node/.openclaw\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace\"\n      # Compatibility aliases for old paths already used in-session.\n      # Keep for now, remove later once path usage is normalized.\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Raw:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/raw\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Clean:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/clean\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Database:/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/vault/database\"\n    depends_on:\n      ollama:\n        condition: service_healthy\n    command: [\"node\", \"dist/index.js\", \"gateway\"]\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - node\n        - -e\n        - |\n          const net=require('net');\n          const s=net.connect({host:'127.0.0.1',port:18789},()=>{s.end();process.exit(0)});\n          s.on('error',()=>process.exit(1));\n          setTimeout(()=>process.exit(1),3000);\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 45s\n\n  # =========================================================\n  # 3. THE PURIFIER\n  # =========================================================\n  docling:\n    image: ghcr.io/docling-project/docling-serve:latest\n    container_name: docling\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 30s\n    ports:\n      - \"5001:5001\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Raw:/root/apollo_raw\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Clean:/root/apollo_clean\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - python\n        - -c\n        - |\n          import socket; s=socket.socket(); s.settimeout(3); s.connect((\"127.0.0.1\",5001)); s.close()\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 45s\n\n  # =========================================================\n  # 4. THE MEMORY\n  # =========================================================\n  lightrag:\n    image: ghcr.io/hkuds/lightrag:latest\n    container_name: apollo-lightrag\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 45s\n    ports:\n      - \"9621:9621\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Database:/app/data/rag_storage\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault/Clean:/app/data/inputs\"\n    environment:\n      LLM_BINDING: \"ollama\"\n      LLM_BINDING_HOST: \"http://ollama:11434\"\n      LLM_MODEL: \"Apollo-Architect\"\n      EMBEDDING_BINDING: \"ollama\"\n      EMBEDDING_BINDING_HOST: \"http://ollama:11434\"\n      EMBEDDING_MODEL: \"nomic-embed-text\"\n      SUMMARY_CONTEXT_SIZE: \"32000\"\n    depends_on:\n      ollama:\n        condition: service_healthy\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - python\n        - -c\n        - |\n          import socket; s=socket.socket(); s.settimeout(3); s.connect((\"127.0.0.1\",9621)); s.close()\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 60s\n\n  # =========================================================\n  # 5. THE SCOUTS\n  # =========================================================\n  browserless:\n    image: browserless/chrome:latest\n    container_name: browserless\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 30s\n    ports:\n      - \"3003:3000\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - node\n        - -e\n        - |\n          const net=require('net');\n          const s=net.connect({host:'127.0.0.1',port:3000},()=>{s.end();process.exit(0)});\n          s.on('error',()=>process.exit(1));\n          setTimeout(()=>process.exit(1),3000);\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 45s\n\n  crawl4ai:\n    image: unclecode/crawl4ai:latest\n    container_name: apollo-scout\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 30s\n    ports:\n      - \"11235:11235\"\n    environment:\n      MAX_CONCURRENT_TASKS: \"3\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - python\n        - -c\n        - |\n          import socket; s=socket.socket(); s.settimeout(3); s.connect((\"127.0.0.1\",11235)); s.close()\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 45s\n\n  # =========================================================\n  # 6. THE CONDUCTORS\n  # =========================================================\n  # Keep this database service restart-safe, but do not silently migrate n8n\n  # to Postgres in this pass. The current n8n data directory already contains\n  # a live SQLite database, and switching backends here could strand state.\n  n8n_db:\n    image: postgres:16\n    container_name: n8n_db\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 60s\n    environment:\n      POSTGRES_USER: \"apollo_admin\"\n      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: \"${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}\"\n      POSTGRES_DB: \"apollo_state\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"./data/postgres:/var/lib/postgresql/data\"\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD-SHELL\n        - pg_isready -U $$POSTGRES_USER -d $$POSTGRES_DB\n      interval: 20s\n      timeout: 5s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 20s\n\n\n--- .env ---\nAPOLLO_TOKEN=ccad98cef794f550490712c8093668bc63ce6479e2d67d5c\nPOSTGRES_PASSWORD=secure_password_2026\nWEBUI_SECRET_KEY=apollo_v2_secret\nN8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY=PteGFZ4agMEMf6Xfd9ry3gb2d29FIVNt"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":16,"aggregated":"services:\n  # =========================================================\n  # 1. THE INFERENCE ENGINE\n  # =========================================================\n  ollama:\n    image: ollama/ollama:latest\n    container_name: ollama\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    init: true\n    stop_grace_period: 60s\n    ports:\n      - \"11434:11434\"\n    volumes:\n      - \"./data/ollama:/root/.ollama\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Intel:/root/apollo_intel\"\n      - \"C:/Apollo/Vault:/root/apollo_vault\"\n    environment:\n      OLLAMA_FLASH_ATTENTION: \"1\"\n      OLLAMA_KV_CACHE_TYPE: \"q4_0\"\n      OLLAMA_NUM_GPU: \"-1\"\n    healthcheck:\n     