{"type":"message","id":"3d9e3b66","parentId":"1a658bab","timestamp":"2026-04-17T06:59:18.018Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Organizing project updates**\n\nI need to verify the contents, but I wonder if it's really necessary. I might use exec grep to help with that. It could be a good time to update the documentation too. I should note the backup rule and remember the backup script did v3. I need to update the project status, checklist, and decisions in status.json and the daily notes. I’ll use edits to keep everything in order.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1da2b2da88191b65b875d065952b8\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp4dotB_Pwlu4xGA4ojaGOVCZpQ7H-LzHY3iFKr_YB7dnBlDrQbVP79BUlHD_3QEJGbbiiQxe15uYBMVa8Kll-xa4o71XtCqiQDfVkS41o51WxFmD55jTel5TTmUl_yuHRdK2M3MXS5OGRiFKfAUty--3yWb_YxuQjQ99wVqYckO3M4-zhx0TAGoBIoqAMxTs07Z99c9MllGk9XuQDBYpkIqrU0c9XwK4p7r3PZeXheDhVtlvMX730-0UoRPyEwEZJCwSF23zKwqxHNDhs9pYkZHRYQcruJrBsC-O0Iz6OKCOmbPdh8b19WOqsVhrrHEgofft3rELAgFCy8xWumpr1vIjs4J1z9oshg4Bv3XyK4fzcd2wxkY-mRscHSQbERMXDCAxMcBqGL-nCcMdDbY9eLf_OGKkKbIIWCgCvTVcMuDKYpUicLf3vT75hwqHkudJtmLycGuF7s7bnVh0aevVlmzpKG9HIB6lXF-lVPboDFMi5KxIDkyqBHuRolwUo1AasFucLIiQlwqsZCpTQhiPSQO7VghSOv2kqfT6dCHnMA0KtQ5_nwbPbO500vh1E_qw1FpexZDhYwtgxevWS07yKY-xO6Wlycf82KvbbZXb3d1OJfikCobM0k2FLyM4UvqVpBeZgbz6ir4-bfodZ8yWInEoBqYM1E_bdDWOR9N40wjqzma56Fe8dph9Q9Z1I1uNKQ9Mv7tcqjAbSkzYOyd9sHEfALSsk-jFoBlKqzeob6goLDs0AEBA4aQ4OE08Z2S7g0YyvU-poVq8KkYyriWMoj5svQFqaGU6wM4ujBAgqvpoEBBFp5RTPSgeN6lln9xr1cwsrdzxGa1lZimv-vRAw-MuObJcXBDsfd7D8Ddl93dON3HvFJK3Ej6FqjKdD2mGakDW3zfCD1i0lp09iM0GlJqnTxM8w86AZrnsTukEc8Zdc9dipEhHbme0Vq-MyIwBrncqZgmavKM0afEJtpq3ZwaLi5q4fzc_ZtGh8BgN_MwKfTFpk3Q-Z_aaLk4w3VItv8r5fMnqty82UUy02Nj9NbfE4qtt4qFLhD4SALfedZ6UWebbYkkmlaLRmVT6G8_Cb7FNN4-RbwjJQKfZRJMOR-T8XQus-qSQK_SeIm9GPTQAsDbxB2p1E-ZezTwt0HRLCKsCxjtHHPd9ntyfYFgpeetLmcAcUpueTAb-SmDhmu2Kj2YZ0QyT4LPriiZZHxJs3EmCkjIb-XVNbhI3RR5pjLNmQhrE5-YCRrGH5S3TvQe6Z1799xLiCYJEhiHY3WB50a0a_\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Organizing project updates**\\n\\nI need to verify the contents, but I wonder if it's really necessary. I might use exec grep to help with that. It could be a good time to update the documentation too. I should note the backup rule and remember the backup script did v3. I need to update the project status, checklist, and decisions in status.json and the daily notes. I’ll use edits to keep everything in order.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"I’ve rewritten both scripts. I’m doing the continuity updates now so future sessions know the batch files are no longer the old “sleep and hope” versions.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1da2dd9588191818b8ba530447eb6\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_g7HFLBG8KbF4Km1ZO1jSrBjh|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1da4638548191b4c312db0b28fec3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,240p' apollo_up.bat && printf '\\n---\\n' && sed -n '1,240p' apollo_down.bat","workdir":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":20},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"sed -n '1,240p' apollo_up.bat && printf '\\\\n---\\\\n' && sed -n '1,240p' apollo_down.bat\",\"workdir\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":20}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_gvhwRCxJxK5b2RbdNwQt0T00|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1da46386c819191844fbebdf50c46","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"projects/apollo/status.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## Immediate next actions\n1. validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\n2. rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness/health rather than fixed sleeps\n3. inspect and validate `Vault/Clean` as the initial retrieval corpus\n4. verify what LightRAG is actually reading from `Vault/Clean`\n5. define and/or verify the indexing path for the clean corpus\n6. prove the admin query loop with canonical Apollo questions\n7. keep secrets and irrelevant runtime debris out of the retrieval surface\n","newText":"## Immediate next actions\n1. validate the hardened compose file and rewritten batch scripts against the live Docker runtime\n2. inspect and validate `Vault/Clean` as the initial retrieval corpus\n3. verify what LightRAG is actually reading from `Vault/Clean`\n4. define and/or verify the indexing path for the clean corpus\n5. prove the admin query loop with canonical Apollo questions\n6. keep secrets and irrelevant runtime debris out of the retrieval surface\n"},{"oldText":"- A first hardening pass has now been applied to `docker-compose.yaml` and `.env`:\n  - restart policies added across services\n  - graceful stop timings added\n  - healthchecks added for core services\n  - compose-managed secrets moved into `.env`\n  - remote-exposed ports intentionally left unchanged\n  - `n8n` was **not** switched to Postgres in this pass, to avoid an implicit state migration away from the existing SQLite-backed runtime\n","newText":"- A first hardening pass has now been applied to `docker-compose.yaml` and `.env`:\n  - restart policies added across services\n  - graceful stop timings added\n  - healthchecks added for core services\n  - compose-managed secrets moved into `.env`\n  - remote-exposed ports intentionally left unchanged\n  - `n8n` was **not** switched to Postgres in this pass, to avoid an implicit state migration away from the existing SQLite-backed runtime\n- `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` have now been rewritten around Docker availability checks, compose detection, health-based waits, ordered shutdown, and stop verification instead of fixed sleeps and optimistic status messages\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"projects/apollo/status.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"## Immediate next actions\\n1. validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\\n2. rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness/health rather than fixed sleeps\\n3. inspect and validate `Vault/Clean` as the initial retrieval corpus\\n4. verify what LightRAG is actually reading from `Vault/Clean`\\n5. define and/or verify the indexing path for the clean corpus\\n6. prove the admin query loop with canonical Apollo questions\\n7. keep secrets and irrelevant runtime debris out of the retrieval surface\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Immediate next actions\\n1. validate the hardened compose file and rewritten batch scripts against the live Docker runtime\\n2. inspect and validate `Vault/Clean` as the initial retrieval corpus\\n3. verify what LightRAG is actually reading from `Vault/Clean`\\n4. define and/or verify the indexing path for the clean corpus\\n5. prove the admin query loop with canonical Apollo questions\\n6. keep secrets and irrelevant runtime debris out of the retrieval surface\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"- A first hardening pass has now been applied to `docker-compose.yaml` and `.env`:\\n  - restart policies added across services\\n  - graceful stop timings added\\n  - healthchecks added for core services\\n  - compose-managed secrets moved into `.env`\\n  - remote-exposed ports intentionally left unchanged\\n  - `n8n` was **not** switched to Postgres in this pass, to avoid an implicit state migration away from the existing SQLite-backed runtime\\n\",\"newText\":\"- A first hardening pass has now been applied to `docker-compose.yaml` and `.env`:\\n  - restart policies added across services\\n  - graceful stop timings added\\n  - healthchecks added for core services\\n  - compose-managed secrets moved into `.env`\\n  - remote-exposed ports intentionally left unchanged\\n  - `n8n` was **not** switched to Postgres in this pass, to avoid an implicit state migration away from the existing SQLite-backed runtime\\n- `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` have now been rewritten around Docker availability checks, compose detection, health-based waits, ordered shutdown, and stop verification instead of fixed sleeps and optimistic status messages\\n\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ML3jgX3cOMw4P6w4npQCTT0S|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1da46387881919444d4fa266fdfd7","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"projects/apollo/checklist.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### F. Runtime hardening\n- [x] Add restart policies and graceful stop settings to core services in `docker-compose.yaml`\n- [x] Add core service healthchecks to `docker-compose.yaml`\n- [ ] Validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\n- [ ] Rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness / health checks\n- [ ] Plan an explicit `n8n` backend migration if Postgres should become authoritative later\n","newText":"### F. Runtime hardening\n- [x] Add restart policies and graceful stop settings to core services in `docker-compose.yaml`\n- [x] Add core service healthchecks to `docker-compose.yaml`\n- [x] Rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness / health checks\n- [ ] Validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\n- [ ] Validate the rewritten batch scripts against the live Docker runtime\n- [ ] Plan an explicit `n8n` backend migration if Postgres should become authoritative later\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"projects/apollo/checklist.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"### F. Runtime hardening\\n- [x] Add restart policies and graceful stop settings to core services in `docker-compose.yaml`\\n- [x] Add core service healthchecks to `docker-compose.yaml`\\n- [ ] Validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\\n- [ ] Rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness / health checks\\n- [ ] Plan an explicit `n8n` backend migration if Postgres should become authoritative later\\n\",\"newText\":\"### F. Runtime hardening\\n- [x] Add restart policies and graceful stop settings to core services in `docker-compose.yaml`\\n- [x] Add core service healthchecks to `docker-compose.yaml`\\n- [x] Rewrite `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` around readiness / health checks\\n- [ ] Validate the hardened compose file against the live Docker runtime\\n- [ ] Validate the rewritten batch scripts against the live Docker runtime\\n- [ ] Plan an explicit `n8n` backend migration if Postgres should become authoritative later\\n\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_gyb10XJmz4tjo22jDW6UK18O|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1da4638848191895527fc33c16b30","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"projects/apollo/decisions.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### Runtime hardening stance\n- Remote access is required, so current port exposure remains intentionally unchanged in this hardening pass\n- `docker-compose.yaml` should be hardened with restart policies, graceful stop periods, and healthchecks across core services\n- Compose-managed secrets should live in `.env`, not inline in `docker-compose.yaml`\n- `n8n` should remain on its current SQLite-backed runtime for now, rather than being silently migrated to Postgres during a hardening pass\n","newText":"### Runtime hardening stance\n- Remote access is required, so current port exposure remains intentionally unchanged in this hardening pass\n- `docker-compose.yaml` should be hardened with restart policies, graceful stop periods, and healthchecks across core services\n- Compose-managed secrets should live in `.env`, not inline in `docker-compose.yaml`\n- `n8n` should remain on its current SQLite-backed runtime for now, rather than being silently migrated to Postgres during a hardening pass\n- `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` should act as readiness-aware lifecycle scripts, not blind wrappers around fixed sleeps or optimistic shutdown messaging\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"projects/apollo/decisions.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"### Runtime hardening stance\\n- Remote access is required, so current port exposure remains intentionally unchanged in this hardening pass\\n- `docker-compose.yaml` should be hardened with restart policies, graceful stop periods, and healthchecks across core services\\n- Compose-managed secrets should live in `.env`, not inline in `docker-compose.yaml`\\n- `n8n` should remain on its current SQLite-backed runtime for now, rather than being silently migrated to Postgres during a hardening pass\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Runtime hardening stance\\n- Remote access is required, so current port exposure remains intentionally unchanged in this hardening pass\\n- `docker-compose.yaml` should be hardened with restart policies, graceful stop periods, and healthchecks across core services\\n- Compose-managed secrets should live in `.env`, not inline in `docker-compose.yaml`\\n- `n8n` should remain on its current SQLite-backed runtime for now, rather than being silently migrated to Postgres during a hardening pass\\n- `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat` should act as readiness-aware lifecycle scripts, not blind wrappers around fixed sleeps or optimistic shutdown messaging\\n\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_rr1uysk0HyTrhB23YMLKL5u1|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1da46389081919d1ecac4d86432b7","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"projects/apollo/status.json","edits":[{"oldText":"    \"validate the hardened docker-compose.yaml against the live runtime\",\n    \"rewrite apollo_up.bat and apollo_down.bat around readiness and health checks\",\n    \"inspect Vault/Clean ingest and classification manifests\",\n","newText":"    \"validate the hardened docker-compose.yaml against the live runtime\",\n    \"validate the rewritten apollo_up.bat and apollo_down.bat against the live runtime\",\n    \"inspect Vault/Clean ingest and classification manifests\",\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"projects/apollo/status.json\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"    \\\"validate the hardened docker-compose.yaml against the live runtime\\\",\\n    \\\"rewrite apollo_up.bat and apollo_down.bat around readiness and health checks\\\",\\n    \\\"inspect Vault/Clean ingest and classification manifests\\\",\\n\",\"newText\":\"    \\\"validate the hardened docker-compose.yaml against the live runtime\\\",\\n    \\\"validate the rewritten apollo_up.bat and apollo_down.bat against the live runtime\\\",\\n    \\\"inspect Vault/Clean ingest and classification manifests\\\",\\n\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_XlorasmBaJSKRR7aMB83H4jj|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1da46389c8191ab5987b81b307ad3","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"memory/2026-04-17.md","edits":[{"oldText":"- Updated Apollo control docs to record the hardening decisions and next validation steps.\n","newText":"- Updated Apollo control docs to record the hardening decisions and next validation steps.\n- Backed up the core project files again as `v3` snapshots before rewriting `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat`.\n- Rewrote `apollo_up.bat` to detect Docker/Compose, wait for health instead of sleeping blindly, and only pull `nomic-embed-text` if it is missing.\n- Rewrote `apollo_down.bat` to do ordered shutdown, verify containers are no longer running, and avoid pretending that `nvidia-smi` itself releases VRAM.\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"memory/2026-04-17.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"- Updated Apollo control docs to record the hardening decisions and next validation steps.\\n\",\"newText\":\"- Updated Apollo control docs to record the hardening decisions and next validation steps.\\n- Backed up the core project files again as `v3` snapshots before rewriting `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat`.\\n- Rewrote `apollo_up.bat` to detect Docker/Compose, wait for health instead of sleeping blindly, and only pull `nomic-embed-text` if it is missing.\\n- Rewrote `apollo_down.bat` to do ordered shutdown, verify containers are no longer running, and avoid pretending that `nvidia-smi` itself releases VRAM.\\n\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":18274,"output":1500,"cacheRead":117248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":137022,"cost":{"input":0.045685,"output":0.0225,"cacheRead":0.029311999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.097497}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776409127996,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b421773016