{"type":"message","id":"0c722f8d","parentId":"3e89654a","timestamp":"2026-04-17T06:59:34.916Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done.\n\nBackups created first as `v3` snapshots in `legacy/Backups/`.\n\nRewritten:\n- `apollo_up.bat`\n- `apollo_down.bat`\n\n## What changed\n\n### `apollo_up.bat`\nNow it:\n- detects `docker compose` vs `docker-compose`\n- verifies Docker daemon is reachable\n- starts `ollama` first\n- waits for **health**, not fixed sleep\n- only pulls `nomic-embed-text` if missing\n- starts the full stack\n- waits for core containers to become healthy\n- only then opens:\n  - `http://localhost:18789`\n  - `http://localhost:3000`\n\n### `apollo_down.bat`\nNow it:\n- detects compose command\n- verifies Docker daemon is reachable\n- stops services in a more sensible order\n- verifies containers are no longer running\n- treats `nvidia-smi` as a status report, not fake VRAM release magic\n- prints a more truthful final status\n\n## Also updated\n- `projects/apollo/status.md`\n- `projects/apollo/checklist.md`\n- `projects/apollo/decisions.md`\n- `projects/apollo/status.json`\n- `memory/2026-04-17.md`\n\n## Important note\nI still **could not live-test** the scripts here because Docker CLI is not available in this current session environment.\n\nSo the next real step is:\n- run `apollo_up.bat`\n- confirm health/start behavior\n- run `apollo_down.bat`\n- confirm clean stop behavior\n\nIf you want, next I can do a **static review pass** on the rewritten batch files for likely Windows batch pitfalls before you run them.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1da510a3c81919504eab815fe76be\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":19872,"output":353,"cacheRead":116224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":136449,"cost":{"input":0.04968,"output":0.005295,"cacheRead":0.029056,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.084031}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp"