heck fails. I'll need to keep an eye on the service name as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Suggesting Pre-Flight Checks**\\n\\nI think it would be a good idea to recommend some pre-flight checks for the user before they run anything. First, ensure that backups exist. Second, check that session transcripts are safe. I should also mention that while the current chat might be lost, the session file will persist. It could be helpful for the user to copy the final response. Lastly, I might suggest mentioning a change or two to the scripts, but only if they're comfortable doing so.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating healthcheck issues**\\n\\nI'm considering that in Docker health checks, if one service doesn’t support healthchecks or if they're misconfigured, the entire startup could fail even if the service seems to be running. The images like docling, lightrag, and crawl4ai likely have Python-based probes, but I'm not sure about open-webui. Others like browserless/chrome and n8n are confirmed as Node-based. I see potential issues with how services are named and that verifying stopped containers might misclassify them if not created. There's a moderate risk involved due to unknown healthcheck statuses.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing healthcheck risks**\\n\\nI think the biggest lingering risk isn't the scripts but the healthchecks. If those fail, the startup script will abort, so I should advise the user to manually check `docker compose ps` or `logs`. Saving a transcript may not be strictly necessary, but it could be helpful. Since the session is inside the apollo-agent container, running apollo_down might stop the current session, potentially causing a disconnection. I need to make sure the user is aware of this and also confirm the session transcript's file path. Finally, I’ll verify we have no missing labels or batch syntax bugs.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_RdxDx5Etp8C9WdIrdUKqmP75|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1dc0ba9a88191aee4adcc668ba807","name":"update_plan","arguments":{"explanation":"Reviewed both batch files for syntax and lifecycle logic, and identified the main operational risks before restart.","plan":[{"step":"Read the rewritten batch files in full","status":"completed"},{"step":"Review for Windows batch pitfalls and Docker/Compose edge cases","status":"completed"},{"step":"Summarize risk level, likely failure points, and recommended pre-flight checks","status":"completed"}]},"partialJson":"{\"explanation\":\"Reviewed both batch files for syntax and lifecycle logic, and identified the main operational risks before restart.\",\"plan\":[{\"step\":\"Read the rewritten batch files in full\",\"status\":\"completed\"},{\"step\":\"Review for Windows batch pitfalls and Docker/Compose edge cases\",\"status\":\"completed\"},{\"step\":\"Summarize risk level, likely failure points, and recommended pre-flight checks\",\"status\":\"completed\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":20223,"output":975,"cacheRead":113152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134350,"cost":{"input":0.050557500000000005,"output":0.014625,"cacheRead":0.028287999999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0934705}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776409588618,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1dbf5266c8191855b16cf674934e0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f1faad5f","parentId":"43cd3096","timestamp":"2026-04-17T07:06:52.346Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_RdxDx5Etp8C9WdIrdUKqmP75|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1dc0ba9a88191aee4adcc668ba807","toolName":"update_plan","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Plan updated."}],"details":{"status":"updated","explanation":"Reviewed both batch files for syntax and lifecycle logic, and identified the main operational risks before restart.","plan":[{"step":"Read the rewritten batch files in full","status":"completed"},{"step":"Review for Windows batch pitfalls and Docker/Compose edge cases","status":"completed"},{"step":"Summarize risk level, likely failure points, and recommended pre-flight checks","status":"completed"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776409612340}}
{"type":"message","id":"24736cc7","parentId":"f1faad5f","timestamp":"2026-04-17T07:07:06.910Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good call. Static review verdict:\n\n## Bottom line\nI do **not** see an obvious Windows batch syntax bug in either script.\nThey look **reasonable to run**.\n\n## What looks good\n\n### `apollo_up.bat`\n- detects `docker compose` vs `docker-compose`\n- checks Docker daemon first\n- starts `ollama` before the rest\n- waits on health instead of blind sleep\n- only pulls `nomic-embed-text` if missing\n- fails fast on errors\n- opens the URLs only after health checks pass\n\n### `apollo_down.bat`\n- checks Docker/Compose first\n- stops services in a sensible order\n- verifies they’re no longer running\n- treats missing containers as acceptable\n- avoids pretending `nvidia-smi` itself does shutdown work\n\n## Main remaining risks\n\n### 1. The biggest risk is **not** batch syntax, it’s healthcheck realism\nIf any service healthcheck is wrong for its image, `apollo_up.bat` will fail even if the container is technically running.\n\nMost likely fragile spots:\n- `docling`\n- `lightrag`\n- `crawl4ai`\n- maybe `open-webui`\n\nReason:\n- those healthchecks assume the image has `python`\n- that is probably true, but not guaranteed until tested\n\n### 2. Running `apollo_down.bat` will likely kill this current session\nThat part is expected.\nBecause `apollo-agent` is part of the stack, the active OpenClaw webchat session may drop during shutdown.\n\n### 3. Compose health dependency behavior can still differ by host setup\nThe scripts themselves look fine, but actual success depends on:\n- Docker Desktop running normally\n- compose honoring the updated file as expected\n- the containers starting cleanly under the new config\n\n## My confidence level\n- **Batch syntax:** high confidence\n- **Operational success:** moderate confidence\n- **Biggest uncertainty:** healthchecks inside certain images\n\n## What I recommend before you run it\n\n### Minimal pre-flight\n1. keep this note handy\n2. assume the chat session may disconnect\n3. if possible, copy these commands somewhere local first:\n   - `apollo_down.bat`\n   - `apollo_up.bat`\n\n### If restart fails, likely fallback checks on the host\nThese are the first things I’d want run afterward:\n\n- `docker compose ps`\n- `docker compose logs --tail=100 ollama`\n- `docker compose logs --tail=100 apollo-agent`\n- `docker compose logs --tail=100 open-webui`\n- `docker compose logs --tail=100 lightrag`\n- `docker compose logs --tail=100 docling`\n\n## My recommendation\nI think it is **reasonable to proceed**.\n\nIf something breaks, the most likely cause is:\n- one or more healthchecks being too strict or using a missing binary\n\nnot a broken batch file structure.\n\nIf you want, before you run it I can give you a **very short recovery playbook**:\n- what to check first\n- what to ignore\n- what to paste back to me after restart if something fails","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1dc0f744c81918ea8821e636bd3f9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3580,"output":646,"cacheRead":130560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134786,"cost":{"input":0.008950000000000001,"output":0.00969,"cacheRead":0.032639999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.05128}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776409612350,"responseId":"resp_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1dc0cd3ec81919fe47a7db2791ae8"}}
