{"type":"message","id":"d5ca1073","parentId":"1ce3c0f9","timestamp":"2026-04-17T07:24:14.036Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering execution methods**\n\nI'm exploring options for adding small host-side wrapper scripts like `apollo_ps.bat`, which might help with logging and restarting. But if I run these scripts inside a container, they would invoke a Linux shell instead of a Windows batch file, which isn't ideal. Running OpenClaw on the host might be a better choice, giving it direct access to Docker Desktop. However, I need to keep in mind that Docker access is essentially root-level access, so security implications are critical here.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1e012b3508191b7b09bd08702f49e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp4eAeobrIg25pzWyx3TPfnXGs7c3xcBM8Jt7Lod8mzzaJfDVbQh2bIzeT3M6fztvTf6ATgMOZ6qGjlcKCqRVRzsQ_tgHI2NRa4NjDIgBPWY23GU3UuEcaYLvl6prklRcpD0kS0PzQow8cYEOK1ZdxFZ5tqPVfFvyMOVQ8cYLWydCu7GbrmVC_LDmRd7TTtKoP4e5IONVKjkxxcvhJWEjYyOySJlton2Cr8AqhJgvNsujHsw4_81UM1_roB8lPUeUY1lyLdJ_vNLLmGU88XgiBZvFqKeABUfDtVoibic_EZBz-Q1XHkLaiNzjbadMIZkt-g-SAEcBRsjfs80830s48jRSAvWgIO5k49vQb6qcLM924g_e2TZNlhIS6Ah8m1hPgARrN8nKikY5Ilpr53yUx88E9q_R0r43NVNI8iv8qUNvwMvg_4JTDr53RNOKcDz0GVjStxjRFggnuEWp49IXi7ZFzreeikErgmO0A_8S1bAUJK8I2pnyE5UAuuLd2Q9CpXo1txvFmSpLcQRQZcDEOKwigTbSu68PtDCyWsln4BEMC2ddtqrXmSuiCXTYR1L3Y-2xOVyu9FyQBnAZnN9ZlJDz5p_DFhrlE-ntFE7vXQwvlB4RpFRcXlmItL2t_M9eKheZUQpM5qaIHeJlsZ_BmkXbXX8-jQaen6ZN2gskeTSCCGcTBLS7esTvw45Zz-4QZAJYxAC8Nai7jtHnJUGmZMI6aACnGcq-O07Hbl9kO0IZGien2jiHc68-ks306KTuK5yHJLPDUV0LaZ9SAzz8G1bbNugd_PK-j80NLCOV6RUum29eJfRNwBaZmkKz9JykQFOPQTe0KvS2QmMYMLRdHbrMjwCXGry0stN4QqkzvRCCxhr3S-1qVhHLYsSGYXjBCShu2F5qkD7OBk0zwhUFbrdWmOCi6y7yoCMGX0g2JxOnUaydEZ3BcXtihFriUPvTeIm72oxtb75Hm8hXKYQP13iiOYMOt6WGBnacmiJvXlcaDmogOZ2vBO1Xdd_LNj_bEI-RX2qty61OtUX6eJO6obSjbqpANV5nwb4GoF9zIIr3TOIcV6QnS3iYpzINDiTXtLKVdVT5Em70VfaVhnlOL7jE6ql_V8-OA4R5KXJLFIkHfZf6sPPv0ZZ9eRetUtd9QVXtYmRG-Mi