emory/2026-04-17.md#L1-L12\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"3f6075d286184b913f5a4b1347fcd9dcef5d7e3013abf4144f5e1e91109d3f29\",\n      \"path\": \"MEMORY.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 37,\n      \"endLine\": 45,\n      \"score\": 0.3409816424653573,\n      \"textScore\": 0.3409816424653573,\n      \"snippet\": \"- Do not ingest secrets or irrelevant runtime debris casually.\\n- Preserve explicit project boundaries: Apollo, Aurelius, Shared, Other.\\n- Before modifying core project/runtime files such as `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and similar core files, create a dated/versioned backup in `legacy/Backups/`.\\n\\n## Memory durability rule\\n- `MEMORY.md` matters and should not silently disappear.\\n- If `MEMORY.md` is ever missing in a main session, restore it from `memory/backups/MEMORY.latest.md` if available, otherwise reconstruct it from recent daily notes and canonical project files, then tell the user.\\n- After meaningful edits to `MEMORY.md`, keep a mirrored backup in\\n\\nSource: MEMORY.md#L37-L45\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"MEMORY.md#L37-L45\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"none\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\",\n  \"mode\": \"fts-only\"\n}"}],"details":{"results":[{"id":"cf3614742a84cfd0d7f0dc21f4a0ccc896b6c07e697c5c09ce8059b54dab8212","path":"memory/backups/MEMORY-2026-04-17.md","startLine":20,"endLine":41,"score":0.4170328138063223,"textScore":0.4170328138063223,"snippet":"## Canonical project continuity\n- `projects/apollo/` is the canonical control surface for Apollo.\n- `Vault/Clean/` is the curated corpus / evidence layer.\n- `Vault/raw/` is the raw archive layer.\n- Apollo continuity should not rely on chat history alone. The project control files must stay current.\n\n## Apollo, recovered project progress\n- The running stack already includes OpenClaw, Ollama, Open WebUI, LightRAG, Docling, Browserless, Crawl4AI, and n8n + Postgres.\n- The repo root is the active OpenClaw workspace roo