durable Apollo context and continuity rules.\n- Added a `memory/backups/` backup path and a simple backup script so future `MEMORY.md` changes can be mirrored.\n- Updated `AGENTS.md` with instructions to restore `MEMORY.md` f\n\nSource: memory/2026-04-17.md#L1-L12","source":"memory","citation":"memory/2026-04-17.md#L1-L12"},{"id":"3f6075d286184b913f5a4b1347fcd9dcef5d7e3013abf4144f5e1e91109d3f29","path":"MEMORY.md","startLine":37,"endLine":45,"score":0.3409816424653573,"textScore":0.3409816424653573,"snippet":"- Do not ingest secrets or irrelevant runtime debris casually.\n- Preserve explicit project boundaries: Apollo, Aurelius, Shared, Other.\n- Before modifying core project/runtime files such as `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and similar core files, create a dated/versioned backup in `legacy/Backups/`.\n\n## Memory durability rule\n- `MEMORY.md` matters and should not silently disappear.\n- If `MEMORY.md` is ever missing in a main session, restore it from `memory/backups/MEMORY.latest.md` if available, otherwise reconstruct it from recent daily notes and canonical project files, then tell the user.\n- After meaningful edits to `MEMORY.md`, keep a mirrored backup in\n\nSource: MEMORY.md#L37-L45","source":"memory","citation":"MEMORY.md#L37-L45"}],"provider":"none","citations":"auto","mode":"fts-only"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776410654526}}
{"type":"message","id":"30bd4a1c","parentId":"cbbf8154","timestamp":"2026-04-17T07:24:42.158Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering Docker configurations**\n\nI need to note some exact changes at a high level. First, I should add the volume `/var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock`. Then, I can either use a custom image with docker-cli and the compose plugin or install the package during the build. \n\nI’m thinking about group permissions and running as either root or the docker group. Since the docker socket is root-owned and the container runs as the node user, I might need to handle permissions carefully. Also, I want to remember to mention any Windows-specific issues. Let's present this with numbered choices and a recommendation.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1e022b2e481919b08f04e330aa8d9\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp4eAr_tjgZ5lODHDwm6XXGdH587pOjJ06HkToStMsaL0Uih8l1DP7kqAcjvE_WlBkfl-EyN5w_YiIjqv9ddWp-IAxAYjUuWRmSxcn3AzXDawOYn0QWOJloJiD-qi7Z_kd3zWGDfhnq5OGAkhsf89qUx9aHdn7nlaUEMvD9o_KDG1GYHJkZMCcpzukodJ7i_EBbkU24QGZDrqJZDeZZWRGm_2qJ8fzbLszLWKwfSrnH5tWy4zzDIT6Q_CJTlifIISkeOIlQ_AZVrfq0vFlIVE32DuKjSNgTXLrZ2FU9i8gIuJpulDz5UdqCoSgWApvVbt8qn6dSgjF-uqAB7AN5_4xZsqCyEwstyTwa72gcvG_w43zenuAXEo08YDwy-zZzfDYO9yl2pB3sL-BW-mKdUPsAk0V8Zu15TeD9nDUNW8WlWr3FchjuS22I-943EdVsPsutx2Cxi1YQBriNNg4D55GWD8Yj8_qHOuxgpoVaJ-zLHeW3ZQdg61uw_LxW-5A8JU9NOy40gcFbmBy2cO-Lfhltbk9bcNsMuqd8PE2meerKwhHTVrvBHqw21DvFh0_eyVM7tKV-YAIlvYU4x1N5tcFB_KBG-5OF5w-u0CzFU7-bkUN5cdFqUTiLkpzquA1kfPsC0GdZe5J78TeW2vLNH-l7_PQ_9miEXSmefbSC0Ap_JwJVP8qcGlxdHldDPgXcOk10EorGzLxFwifrdPS0xxYi5eLiDgJaYqs06f61VbXXD6tHzeyk-GqfkUiqOPD_q6GaUJBZuobhBtF_tEDsD1mG4jGpi8tTVC1iHM0SNvTI9jnCUm3ACGNOGIf-usIPrkC3U6PiS_DTnAaxGLt12t5NubhNrs9l2xfjm7I2FT2iZK1NcmNZRtko6LI5OPWEEFntnLjikBAovl2Lp0r6Y5ktEQUmEQLi1RAbXFMPWmGl_Y-ZAzmudL6EIhmRcQJYsoMhyhmJ4K3pm7FnURHhuHlS2zRs8TN38CJFE5nV6yIwIV9BNX1SXPXWPi_dG-fJEFUojWDmPp5riJ31bT1ppISk47n63oe6VOtLm5Qqe