text.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1e9176cb08191b7762c0bb565811b\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_tggEA2Y9NJhjcxCCyTFuEdto|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1e91786708191b41faadc40b16cbf","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"legacy/Recovered-Sessions/2026-04-17-lost-session-recovery.md","content":"# Lost Session Recovery - 2026-04-17\n\nThis note reconstructs the key Apollo conversations recovered from saved OpenClaw session transcripts in `Intel/agents/main/sessions/`.\n\n## 1. Immediate lost-thread recovery\n\nRecovered from:\n- `5c3a7f85-0d14-4d10-a540-96977da5f241.jsonl`\n\n### Exact recovered exchange\n\n**User, 2026-04-17 04:01 UTC**\n> ok lets proceed to definig contract then\n\n**Assistant**\n> Yes, let’s define the contract.\n>\n> Here’s a clean starting structure we can fill in together:\n> 1. Purpose and scope\n> 2. Parties involved\n> 3. Deliverables\n> 4. Timeline and milestones\n> 5. Roles and responsibilities\n> 6. Payment / consideration\n> 7. Acceptance criteria\n> 8. Change process\n> 9. Confidentiality\n> 10. Termination\n> 11. Dispute / governing terms\n> 12. Sign-off\n>\n> If you want, I can draft a first-pass contract now.\n>\n> Just send me either:\n> - the actual deal terms, or\n> - even rough notes/bullets\n>\n> and I’ll turn them into contract language.\n\n### What happened next\nFive minutes later the user reported that the PC had gone into standby, the session/chat history appeared lost, and Apollo continuity recovery began from project files.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Apollo corpus-ingestion and structuring session\n\nRecovered from:\n- `95ab2a64-b730-4d1a-b975-fbff48fab4e2.jsonl.reset.2026-04-16T08-08-02.405Z`\n\n### Key recovered outcomes\nThis session contained the first major corpus-preparation work for Apollo and Aurelius.\n\nRecovered milestones:\n- structured-memory corpus approach chosen over a single giant merged file\n- decision to tag conversation entries by project, concatenate by project, preserve per-entry provenance, and generate summary docs\n- corpus inventory and dedupe pass completed\n- created:\n  - `vault/Clean/reports/raw_manifest.json`\n  - `vault/Clean/reports/exact_duplicates.json`\n  - `vault/Clean/reports/probable_duplicates.json`\n  - `vault/Clean/reports/raw_corpus_report.md`\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/classification.json`\n- created project buckets:\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/apollo/sources/`\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/aurelius/sources/`\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/other/sources/`\n- refinement and timeline pass completed\n- created:\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/classification_refined.json`\n  - `vault/Clean/reports/canonical_corpus_report.md`\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/apollo/timeline.md`\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/aurelius/timeline.md`\n  - scaffold docs for `master_context.md`, `decisions.md`, `tasks.md`, `deliverables.md`\n\n### Important recovered intent\nApollo was explicitly being shaped into a system able to:\n- reconstruct previous project discussions cleanly\n- distinguish Apollo from Aurelius and other projects\n- generate concise mission tasking, steps, and deliverables\n- eventually support agent orchestration from structured project memory\n\n---\n\n## 3. Apollo control-layer creation session\n\nRecovered from:\n- `1a218bee-b0ee-4a58-8724-239ef5ecf788.jsonl.reset.2026-04-17T04-01-07.400Z`\n\n### Key recovered outcomes\nThis session established `projects/apollo/` as the canonical control folder.\n\nRecovered milestones:\n- user provided the live `docker-compose.yaml` and expanded repo access\n- repo root became the visible workspace root\n- legacy nested workspace was sanitized and archived under `legacy/`\n- Apollo control docs were created and normalized:\n  - `README.md`\n  - `charter.md`\n  - `status.md`\n  - `decisions.md`\n  - `deliverables.md`\n  - `checklist.md`\n  - `roadmap.md`\n  - `architecture.md`\n  - `handoff.md`\n  - `sources.md`\n  - `status.json`\n- `AGENTS.md` was updated so future sessions treat `projects/apollo/` as canonical\n\n### Important recovered conceptual decision\nWhen asked what the next conceptual step was, the answer recovered from the transcript was:\n- not more architecture\n- not ingestion yet\n- first define Apollo’s **first proof of usefulness**\n- specifically: Apollo should first prove grounded project cognition over its own planning corpus\n\n---\n\n## 4. Apollo system-definition session\n\nRecovered from:\n- `6eda9e5b-e43c-4e1d-9b5f-caf6e072e2d6.jsonl`\n\n### Key recovered outcomes\nThis session focused on Apollo as a system, not just the current tool stack.\n\nRecovered framing:\n- Apollo should not be treated as random tools glued together\n- Apollo is a governed cognition/action system\n- architecture stance:\n  - OpenClaw = orchestration/control\n  - LightRAG = knowledge substrate / retrieval\n  - Open WebUI = human-facing surface\n  - local models by default, cloud models only when justified\n- emphasis on one governing assistant, not one monolith\n\n---\n\n## Recovered continuity summary\n\nThe lost work was not actually gone. The following project continuity was recovered from transcripts:\n\n1. Apollo and Aurelius corpus structuring had already begun and produced real artifacts.\n2. `projects/apollo/` had already been established as the canonical project continuity layer.\n3. The intended next conceptual step had already been identified: prove Apollo’s first usefulness through grounded cognition over the planning corpus.\n4. The immediate lost-thread message about \"defining the contract\" was recovered exactly.\n\n---\n\n## Recommended use of this recovery note\n\nUse this file when a future session needs to reconstruct:\n- what happened just before the standby-related reset\n- what Apollo control artifacts were created\n- what corpus-processing work was already done\n- what conceptual next step had already been decided\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"legacy/Recovered-Sessions/2026-04-17-lost-session-recovery.md\",\"content\":\"# Lost Session Recovery - 2026-04-17\\n\\nThis note reconstructs the key Apollo conversations recovered from saved OpenClaw session transcripts in `Intel/agents/main/sessions/`.\\n\\n## 1. Immediate lost-thread recovery\\n\\nRecovered from:\\n- `5c3a7f85-0d14-4d10-a540-96977da5f241.jsonl`\\n\\n### Exact recovered exchange\\n\\n**User, 2026-04-17 04:01 UTC**\\n> ok lets proceed to definig contract then\\n\\n**Assistant**\\n> Yes, let’s define the contract.\\n>\\n> Here’s a clean starting structure we can fill in together:\\n> 1. Purpose and scope\\n> 2. Parties involved\\n> 3. Deliverables\\n> 4. Timeline and milestones\\n> 5. Roles and responsibilities\\n> 6. Payment / consideration\\n> 7. Acceptance criteria\\n> 8. Change process\\n> 9. Confidentiality\\n> 10. Termination\\n> 11. Dispute / governing terms\\n> 12. Sign-off\\n>\\n> If you want, I can draft a first-pass contract now.\\n>\\n> Just send me either:\\n> - the actual deal terms, or\\n> - even rough notes/bullets\\n>\\n> and I’ll turn them into contract language.\\n\\n### What happened next\\nFive minutes later the user reported that the PC had gone into standby, the session/chat history appeared lost, and Apollo continuity recovery began from project files.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Apollo corpus-ingestion and structuring session\\n\\nRecovered from:\\n- `95ab2a64-b730-4d1a-b975-fbff48fab4e2.jsonl.reset.2026-04-16T08-08-02.405Z`\\n\\n### Key recovered outcomes\\nThis session contained the first major corpus-preparation work for Apollo and Aurelius.\\n\\nRecovered milestones:\\n- structured-memory corpus approach chosen over a single giant merged file\\n- decision to tag conversation entries by project, concatenate by project, preserve per-entry provenance, and generate summary docs\\n- corpus inventory and dedupe pass completed\\n- created:\\n  - `vault/Clean/reports/raw_manifest.json`\\n  - `vault/Clean/reports/exact_duplicates.json`\\n  - `vault/Clean/reports/probable_duplicates.json`\\n  - `vault/Clean/reports/raw_corpus_report.md`\\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/classification.json`\\n- created project buckets:\\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/apollo/sources/`\\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/aurelius/sources/`\\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/other/sources/`\\n- refinement and timeline pass completed\\n- created:\\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/classification_refined.json`\\n  - `vault/Clean/reports/canonical_corpus_report.md`\\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/apollo/timeline.md`\\n  - `vault/Clean/projects/aurelius/timeline.md`\\n  - scaffold docs for `master_context.md`, `decisions.md`, `tasks.md`, `deliverables.md`\\n\\n### Important recovered intent\\nApollo was explicitly being shaped into a system able to:\\n- reconstruct previous project discussions cleanly\\n- distinguish Apollo from Aurelius and other projects\\n- generate concise mission tasking, steps, and deliverables\\n- eventually support agent orchestration from structured project memory\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Apollo control-layer creation session\\n\\nRecovered from:\\n- `1a218bee-b0ee-4a58-8724-239ef5ecf788.jsonl.reset.2026-04-17T04-01-07.400Z`\\n\\n### Key recovered outcomes\\nThis session established `projects/apollo/` as the canonical control folder.\\n\\nRecovered milestones:\\n- user provided the live `docker-compose.yaml` and expanded repo access\\n- repo root became the visible workspace root\\n- legacy nested workspace was sanitized and archived under `legacy/`\\n- Apollo control docs were created and normalized:\\n  - `README.md`\\n  - `charter.md`\\n  - `status.md`\\n  - `decisions.md`\\n  - `deliverables.md`\\n  - `checklist.md`\\n  - `roadmap.md`\\n  - `architecture.md`\\n  - `handoff.md`\\n  - `sources.md`\\n  - `status.json`\\n- `AGENTS.md` was updated so future sessions treat `projects/apollo/` as canonical\\n\\n### Important recovered conceptual decision\\nWhen asked what the next conceptual step was, the answer recovered from the transcript was:\\n- not more architecture\\n- not ingestion yet\\n- first define Apollo’s **first proof of usefulness**\\n- specifically: Apollo should first prove grounded project cognition over its own planning corpus\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. Apollo system-definition session\\n\\nRecovered from:\\n- `6eda9e5b-e43c-4e1d-9b5f-caf6e072e2d6.jsonl`\\n\\n### Key recovered outcomes\\nThis session focused on Apollo as a system, not just the current tool stack.\\n\\nRecovered framing:\\n- Apollo should not be treated as random tools glued together\\n- Apollo is a governed cognition/action system\\n- architecture stance:\\n  - OpenClaw = orchestration/control\\n  - LightRAG = knowledge substrate / retrieval\\n  - Open WebUI = human-facing surface\\n  - local models by default, cloud models only when justified\\n- emphasis on one governing assistant, not one monolith\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Recovered continuity summary\\n\\nThe lost work was not actually gone. The following project continuity was recovered from transcripts:\\n\\n1. Apollo and Aurelius corpus structuring had already begun and produced real artifacts.\\n2. `projects/apollo/` had already been established as the canonical project continuity layer.\\n3. The intended next conceptual step had already been identified: prove Apollo’s first usefulness through grounded cognition over the planning corpus.\\n4. The immediate lost-thread message about \\\"defining the contract\\\" was recovered exactly.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Recommended use of this recovery note\\n\\nUse this file when a future session needs to reconstruct:\\n- what happened just before the standby-related reset\\n- what Apollo control artifacts were created\\n- what corpus-processing work was already done\\n- what conceptual next step had already been decided\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":31955,"output":1692,"cacheRead":94720,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128367,"cost":{"input":0.0798875,"output":0.02538,"cacheRead":0.02368,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.1289475}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp"