{"type":"message","id":"07b7a9cf","parentId":"d013b594","timestamp":"2026-04-17T08:05:53.168Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_waBMkGMbiparpWpo639OHCIU|fc_02ad8e5e7b4217730169e1e9e0de508191a36db7a35fb55b10","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-17\n\n- The root `MEMORY.md` was discovered missing after the session history was lost when the PC went into standby.\n- Searched for old memory copies. `Intel/memory.md` exists but only contained a test line, so it was not useful as a real recovery source.\n- Recovered Apollo continuity from `projects/apollo/` control docs and from the archived session note `legacy/Intel/workspace/memory/2026-04-16-lightrag-ingestion.md`.\n- Rebuilt a fresh root `MEMORY.md` with the durable Apollo context and continuity rules.\n- Added a `memory/backups/` backup path and a simple backup script so future `MEMORY.md` changes can be mirrored.\n- Updated `AGENTS.md` with instructions to restore `MEMORY.md` from backup if it ever goes missing again.\n- Added a local `scripts/memory_backup_daemon.sh` watchdog and started it with a 10-minute interval so `MEMORY.md` is backed up automatically.\n- The user added a new workspace rule: before modifying core project/runtime files like `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and similar files, create dated/versioned backups in `legacy/Backups/`.\n- Seeded `legacy/Backups/` with backups of `docker-compose.yaml`, `apollo_up.bat`, `apollo_down.bat`, `.env`, and `AGENTS.md`, and added `scripts/backup_core_project_files.sh` to make that easier to follow consistently.\n- Backed up `docker-compose.yaml` and `.env` again as `v2` snapshots before hardening them.\n- Hardened `docker-compose.yaml` with restart policies, `init: true`, graceful stop periods, and core service healthchecks, while keeping remote-access port exposure unchanged.\n- Moved compose-managed secrets into `.env` and added `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `WEBUI_SECRET_KEY`, and the existing `N8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY` there.\n- Deliberately did **not** switch `n8n` to Postgres in this pass, to avoid silently stranding the existing SQLite-backed state.\n- Updated Apollo control docs to record the hardening decisions and next validation steps.\n- Backed up the core project files again as `v3` snapshots before rewriting `apollo_up.bat` and `apollo_down.bat`.\n- Rewrote `apollo_up.bat` to detect Docker/Compose, wait for health instead of sleeping blindly, and only pull `nomic-embed-text` if it is missing.\n- Rewrote `apollo_down.bat` to do ordered shutdown, verify containers are no longer running, and avoid pretending that `nvidia-smi` itself releases VRAM.\n- After restart the full Apollo stack came back healthy (`docker-compose ps` showed all core services healthy), and the `MEMORY.md` backup daemon was restarted successfully.\n- Recovered the previously lost session content into `legacy/Recovered-Sessions/2026-04-17-lost-session-recovery.md`, including the exact recovered \"ok lets proceed to definig contract then\" exchange and the key Apollo decisions recovered from saved session transcripts.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776413153166}}
